@roblox/globaltype/AlignPosition.documentation: A constraint used to apply a force towards a location

@roblox/globaltype/AlignPosition.ApplyAt: When true, applies force at center of mass of Attachment0’s parent Part. When false, applied at Attachment0.
@roblox/globaltype/AlignPosition.MaxForc: Maximum force the constraint can apply to achieve its goal. Only used if RigidityEnabled is false.
@roblox/globaltype/AlignPosition.MaxVelo: Maximum speed the Attachment can move when converging. Only used if RigidityEnabled is false.
@roblox/globaltype/AlignPosition.Reactio: When true the constraint will apply force on both Attachments to achieve the goal.
@roblox/globaltype/AlignPosition.Respons: Used to control how quickly the constraint will reach its goal. Higher values will cause the attachments to move together quicker. Value can be between 5 and 200.
@roblox/globaltype/AlignPosition.Rigidit: When set to true, the solver will react as quickly as possible to move the attachments together. When false, the torque is dependent on AlignPosition.MaxForce, AlignPosition.MaxVelocity, and AlignPosition.Responsiveness.

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.documentation: An internal service used by Roblox to collect analytics from CoreScripts.

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.ApiK: PlayFab API key. Must be set in order to use AnalyticsService:FireEvent.
@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire: The player who triggered the custom event. nil if not player related
User defined category. This should be the name of the event
Optional. User defined data, could be a string, a number or a table
No return

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire.documentation: Fires a custom event with a custom event name and data

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire: The player who triggered the economy event
The name of the item
Indicates the acquisition or spending of an in game resource
A user defined category for items. For example, the category could be “Vehicle” or “Weapon”
The amount of the currency
The currency used. Examples: 'gold', 'gems', 'life' etc.

The event location. A dictionary that each key-value represents an entry of location data. The key-value is a string-string pair. With this you can query which are the most popular “stores” then maybe you want to increase/lower the price for the stores.

See the example below:

local location = {
    ["placeDesc"] = "Dungeon1", 
    ["levelDesc"] = "level2",
    ["mapDesc"] = "LeftChamberMap",
    ["storeName"] = "DarkSmith",
    ["userDefindKey"] = "0005"
}
Optional. User defined data, could be a string, a number or a table
No return

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire.documentation: Fire an event used to track player actions pertaining to the in-game economy

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire: The player who triggered the error event, nil if not player related
The specified log level (e.g. Debug, Error)
User defined message

Optional. A dictionary which contains predefined keys including “errorCode” and “stackTrace”. Both keys values are strings. stackTrace is a traceback of the current function call stack

local debugInfo = {
            errorCode = '123',
            stackTrace = debug.traceback()
      }
Optional. User defined data, could be a string, a number or a table
No return

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire.documentation: Fire a log event used to track errors and warnings experienced by players

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire: The player who triggered the event
A user defined category for progression
Indicates the status of the progression

The event location. A dictionary that each key-value represents an entry of location data. The key-value is a string-string pair. With this developers can query where is the most frequent location for a specific progression event category. For example, the category could be “LevelUp”.

local location = {
    ["placeDesc"] = "Dungeon1", 
    ["levelDesc"] = "level2",
    ["mapDesc"] = "LeftChamberMap",
    ["ProgresionType"] = "LevelUp",
    ["userDefindKey5"] = "0005"
}

Optional. A dictionary that each key-value represents an entry of statistics data that allows developers to track any specific data that they want to collect as players progress through their game. Key-Value is a string-number pair.

local statistics = {
    ["numberOfKills"] = 111, 
    ["numberOfExp"] = 222,
    ["userDefindKey3"] = number,
    ["userDefindKey4"] = number,
    ["userDefindKey5"] = number
}
Optional. User defined data, could be a string, a number or a table.
No return

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire.documentation: Fire an event used to track player progression through the game

@roblox/globaltype/AnalyticsService.Fire: The category of event to report. Cannot contain the following characters: comma ,, double quote " or newline characters \r\n
A value to be serialized and reported. Serialized length must not exceed 1 KB, or 1024 bytes
No return

@roblox/globaltype/AngularVelocity.documentation: Applies a constant torque to a Part, relative to an Attachment space or world space

@roblox/globaltype/AngularVelocity.MaxTo: Magnitude of the maximum torque the constraint can apply
@roblox/globaltype/AngularVelocity.React: Causes the constraint to apply equal and opposite reaction forces

@roblox/globaltype/Animation.documentation: An object that references an animation asset (AnimationId) which can be loaded by a Humanoid or AnimationController

@roblox/globaltype/Animation.AnimationId: This property is the content ID of the animation an Animation object is referencing. Once an animation has been created and uploaded to Roblox the content ID can be found in the uploaded animation’s URL.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationController.documentation: An object which allows animations to be loaded and applied to a character or model in place of a Humanoid when a Humanoid is not needed

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationController.G.documentation: Returns an array of all AnimationTrack that are currently being played by the AnimationController.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationController.L.documentation: This function loads an Animation onto an AnimationController, returning an AnimationTrack that can be used for playback.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationController.A.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
This event fires whenever the AnimationController begins playing an animation. It returns the AnimationTrack playing.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.documentation: Controls the playback of an animation on a Humanoid or AnimationController. This object cannot be created, instead it is returned by the Humanoid:LoadAnimation method.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Animat: The Animation object that was used to create this AnimationTrack.
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.IsPlay: A read only property that returns true when the AnimationTrack is playing.
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Length: A read only property that returns the length (in seconds) of an AnimationTrack. This will return 0 until the animation has fully loaded and thus may not be immediately available.
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Looped: This property sets whether the animation will repeat after finishing. If it is changed while playing the result will take effect after the animation finishes.
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Priori: This property sets the priority of an AnimationTrack. Depending on what this is set to, playing multiple animations at once will look to this property to figure out which Keyframe Poses should be played over one another.
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Speed: The Speed of an AnimationTrack is a read only property that gives the current playback speed of the AnimationTrack. This has a default value of 1. When speed is equal to 1, the amount of time an animation takes to complete is equal to AnimationTrack.Length (in seconds).
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.TimePo: Returns the position in time in seconds that an AnimationTrack is through playing its source animation. Can be set to make the track jump to a specific moment in the animation.
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Weight: WeightCurrent is a read-only property that gives the current weight of the AnimationTrack. It has a default value of 1.

WeightCurrent is a read-only property that gives the current weight of the AnimationTrack. It has a default value of 1 and is set when AnimationTrack:Play, AnimationTrack:Stop or AnimationTrack:AdjustWeight is called.
@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Adjust: The playback speed the animation is to be changed to.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Adjust.documentation: This function changes the AnimationTrack.Speed of an animation. A positive value for speed plays the animation forward, a negative one plays it backwards, and 0 pauses it.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Adjust: The weight the animation is to be changed to.
The duration of time that the animation will fade between the old weight and the new weight for.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Adjust.documentation: Changes the weight of an animation, with the optional fadeTime parameter determining how long it takes for AnimationTrack.WeightCurrent to reach AnimationTrack.WeightTarget.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.GetMar: The name of the KeyFrameMarker the signal is being created for.
The signal created and fired when the animation reaches the created KeyFrameMarker.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.GetMar.documentation: This function returns an DataType.RBXScriptSignal that fires when a specified KeyframeMarker has been hit in an Animation

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.GetTim: The name associated with the Keyframe to be found.
The time, in seconds, the Keyframe occurs at normal playback speed.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.GetTim.documentation: Returns the time position of the first Keyframe of the given name in an AnimationTrack.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Play/p: The duration of time that the animation's weight should be faded in for.
The weight the animation is to be played at.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Play.documentation: Plays the AnimationTrack. Once called an AnimationTrack will play with the specified fadeTime, weight and speed.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Stop/p: The time, in seconds, for which animation weight is to be faded out over.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Stop.documentation: Stops the AnimationTrack. Once called playback of the AnimationTrack will stop and the weight of the animation will move towards zero over a length of time specified by the optional fadeTime parameter.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.DidLoo.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
This event fires when an AnimationTrack loops on the next update following the end of the previous animation loop.

@roblox/globaltype/AnimationTrack.Keyfra.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires every time playback of an AnimationTrack reaches a Keyframe that does not have the default name - "Keyframe"

@roblox/globaltype/Atmosphere.documentation: The Atmosphere object pushes Roblox closer toward realistic environments where sunlight scatters in different ways depending on density and other air particle properties

@roblox/globaltype/Atmosphere.Color: Changes the Atmosphere hue for subtle environmental moods.
@roblox/globaltype/Atmosphere.Decay:
When used with increased Atmosphere.Haze and Atmosphere.Glare, defines the hue of the Atmosphere away from the sun, gradually falling off from Atmosphere.Color towards this value.

See the articles/Atmosphere|Atmosphere Controls article for property comparisons and example environments.

See also

  • articles/Custom Skyboxes|Custom Skyboxes, outlines how to change the default skybox for games and customize the lighting
  • articles/Post Processing Effects|Post-Processing Effects, outlines how post-processing effects can quickly improve a game's visuals with a variety of customizable filters
@roblox/globaltype/Atmosphere.Density: Defines the amount of particles in the Atmosphere and essentially controls how much in-game objects/terrain will be obscured by them.
@roblox/globaltype/Atmosphere.Glare: When used with increased Atmosphere.Haze, specifies the glow/glare of the Atmosphere around the sun. More glare results in an increased effect of sunlight cast onto the sky and world.
@roblox/globaltype/Atmosphere.Haze: Defines the haziness of the Atmosphere with a visible effect both above the horizon and into the distance.
@roblox/globaltype/Atmosphere.Offset: Controls how light transmits between the camera and the sky background.

@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.documentation: Defines a point and orientation relative to the parent BasePart, typically used with Constraints

@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.Axis: Represents the direction of the X-Axis, relative to the Attachment's Attachment.Rotation, as a unit Vector3 with a length of 1.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.CFrame: Represents the CFrame offset of the Attachment.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.Orientatio: A Vector3 that describes the orientation of the Attachment relative to the orientation of its parent, in degrees. Rotations are applied in Z, X, Y order.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.Position: A Vector3 that describes the positional offset of the Attachment, relative to the position and orientation of its parent.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.SecondaryA: Represents the direction of the Y-Axis, relative to the Attachment's Attachment.Rotation, as a unit Vector3 with a length of 1.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.Visible: Toggles the visibility of the Attachment in-game.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.WorldAxis: Represents the direction of the Attachment|Attachment's Attachment/Axis|X-Axisrelative to the world, as a unitDataType.Vector3` with a length of 1
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.WorldCFram: Describes the exact CFrame of the attachment in world-space coordinates
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.WorldOrien: Describes the orientation (in degrees) of the Attachment relative to the world, rather than the parent of the Attachment.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.WorldPosit: Describes the position of the attachment relative to the world, rather than the parent of the Attachment
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.WorldSecon: Represents the direction of the Attachment/SecondaryAxis|Y-Axis of the Attachment, relative to the world, as a unit DataType.Vector3 with a length of 1
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.Rotation: A Vector3 that describes the rotation of the Attachment relative to the rotation of its parent, in degrees. Rotations are applied in Z, Y, X order.
@roblox/globaltype/Attachment.WorldRotat: Determines the rotation (in degrees) of the attachment relative to the world

@roblox/globaltype/BasePart.Material: Determines the texture and default physical properties of a part
@roblox/globaltype/BasePart.Orientation: Describes the position of the part in the world
@roblox/globaltype/BasePart.PivotOffset: Specifies the offset of the part's pivot from its datatype.CFrame.

Performs a step over operation on the Lua Debugger.

@roblox/globaltype/Decal.documentation: The Decal object is an object which applies an image to a face of a BasePart.

@roblox/globaltype/Decal.LocalTransparen: Acts as a multiplier for the Decal's Decal.Transparency property. The effects are only visible to the local player.
@roblox/globaltype/Decal.Texture: The ContentId of the image to be applied by the Decal.
@roblox/globaltype/Decal.Transparency: Determines the transparency of the Decal with 0 being completely opaque and 1 completely transparent.
@roblox/globaltype/Decal.ZIndex: Determines the rendering order when multiple Decals are assigned the same face

@roblox/globaltype/DepthOfFieldEffect.documentation: Simulates a camera lens by blurring parts of a scene not in focus

@roblox/globaltype/DepthOfFieldEffect.Fo: Distance away from the camera where objects are in focus
@roblox/globaltype/DepthOfFieldEffect.In: Controls the distance away from the DepthOfFieldEffect.FocusDistance where no blur is applied
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.BehaviorType: Sets whether the Dialog can be used by multiple players at once.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.ConversationDi: The furthest distance that I player can be from the Dialog's parent to start a conversation.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.GoodbyeChoiceA: Toggles whether the goodbye option will be displayed.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.GoodbyeDialog: Sets the sentence that the dialog will show to the player when the chat ends
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.InUse: If true, this dialog is being used by at least one player.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.InitialPrompt: Sets the first sentence that the dialog will show to the player, once a chat is commenced.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.Purpose: Sets the icon that the initial dialog displays.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.Tone: Sets the color of the NPC's speech bubble.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.TriggerDistanc: Sets the maximum distance that a dialog can be triggered from.
@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.TriggerOffset: Sets the offset of the dialog relative to the dialog's parent.

@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.GetCurrentPlay.documentation: Returns a list of players currently using the Dialog.

@roblox/globaltype/Dialog.DialogChoiceSe.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a player chooses something to say, through a Dialog instance.

@roblox/globaltype/DialogChoice.GoodbyeC: Toggles whether the goodbye option will be displayed.
@roblox/globaltype/DialogChoice.GoodbyeD: Sets the sentence that the dialog will show to the player when the chat ends
@roblox/globaltype/DialogChoice.Response: Sets what the NPC will say when the player chooses this DialogChoice.
@roblox/globaltype/DialogChoice.UserDial: Sets what the player will say when they choose this DialogChoice.

@roblox/globaltype/Dragger.MouseDown.documentation: Initializes a dragging action, specifying which parts to use when dragging.

@roblox/globaltype/Dragger.MouseUp.documentation: Stops the current dragging action (made by MouseDown)

@roblox/globaltype/DynamicRotate.documentation: The base class for classic motor joints.

@roblox/globaltype/DynamicRotate.BaseAng: The base angle of the DynamicRotate object, in radians.

The output volume of frequencies greater than 4000 Hz.
The output volume of frequencies lower than 400 Hz.
The output volume of frequencies between 400 and 4000 Hz.

@roblox/globaltype/EulerRotationCurve.documentation: Represents a 3D rotation curve, it groups 3 FloatCurve, stored as 3 FloatCurve child instances.

@roblox/globaltype/EulerRotationCurve.Ge.documentation: Samples the 3 FloatCurves (X, Y, Z) at the time passed as argument. Returns the result as 3 Euler angles. If a channel curve is missing or no key is found in the curve the channel is evaluated as nil.
Samples the EulerRotationCurve at a given time and returns the corresponding rotation. Empty Euler angles channels are interpreted as zero.

@roblox/globaltype/EulerRotationCurve.X.documentation: Returns the FloatCurve controlling the X Euler angle channel. It is the first child instance of type FloatCurve named X. If none is found an empty FloatCurve is created.

@roblox/globaltype/EulerRotationCurve.Y.documentation: Returns the FloatCurve controlling the Y channel. It is the first child instance of type FloatCurve named 'Y'. If none is found an empty FloatCurve is created.

@roblox/globaltype/EulerRotationCurve.Z.documentation: Returns the FloatCurve controlling the Z channel. It is the first child instance of type FloatCurve named Z. If none is found an empty FloatCurve is created.

@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.documentation: An Explosion applies force to BaseParts within the explosion's Explosion.BlastRadius. This force breaks joints between parts and kills Humanoid characters not protected by a ForceField.

@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.BlastPressu: Used to determine the amount of force applied to BaseParts caught in the Explosion.BlastRadius.
@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.BlastRadius: This property determines the radius of the Explosion, in studs. This radius determines the area of effect of the explosion, not the size of the explosion's visuals.
@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.DestroyJoin: Used to set the proportion of the Explosion.BlastRadius, between 0 and 1, within which all joints will be destroyed. Anything outside of this range will only have the Explosion force applied to it.

@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.Position: This property is the position of the center of the Explosion. It is defined in world-space and not influenced by the Explosion's parent.
@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.Visible: This property determines whether or not the visual effect of an Explosion is shown or not.

@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.Hit.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.Hit.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Explosion.Hit.documentation: Fires when the Explosion hits a BasePart within its Explosion.BlastRadius. Returns the part hit along with the distance of the part from Explosion.Position.

@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.ChinRais: Raises the chin up; moves the lower lip upwards
Moves the upper lip when ChinRaiser is engaged and touching the upper lip

@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.LeftInne: Raises the interior half of the left brow upwards

@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.LeftLowe: Lowers the lower lip down away from the upper lip revealing the lower teeth

@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.LeftOute: Raises the outer part of the left brow upwards
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.LeftUppe: Raises the left upper lip away from the lower lip revealing the upper teeth
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.LipsToge: Brings the lips together relative to JawDrop
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.LowerLip: Rolls the lower lip up over the teeth
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.Pucker: Makes a kiss-like shape with the mouth
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightDim: Moves the corners of the mouth back in Z
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightEye: Raises the right eyelid upwards to reveal more of the eye white above the iris
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightInn: Raises the interior half of the right brow upwards
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightLip: Lowers the corners of the mouth downwards in a frown
Raises the corners of the mouth upwards in a smile
Stretches the corners of the mouth apart
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightLow: Lowers the lower lip down away from the upper lip revealing the lower teeth
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightNos: Raises the right nostril, pulls the brow down slightly, and wrinkles on the side of the nose
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightOut: Raises the outer part of the right brow upwards
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.RightUpp: Raises the right upper lip away from the lower lip revealing the upper teeth
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.TongueOu: Extends the tip of the tongue out of the mouth
@roblox/globaltype/FaceControls.UpperLip: Rolls the upper lip around the teeth

@roblox/globaltype/FaceInstance.documentation: The FaceInstance class is an abstract class from which the Decal class inherits.

@roblox/globaltype/Feature.documentation: The base class for the legacy motor system.

@roblox/globaltype/Feature.FaceId: Sets what side of the Parent the object is on.
@roblox/globaltype/Feature.InOut: Controls how the Feature is positioned on it's parent's surface, in correspondence to the Feature's Feature.LeftRight and Feature.TopBottom properties.
@roblox/globaltype/Feature.LeftRight: Controls whether the feature is shifted to the left, center, or right on the surface.
@roblox/globaltype/Feature.TopBottom: Controls whether the feature is shifted to the top, center, or bottom on the surface.

@roblox/globaltype/File.documentation: An asset loaded from a file on disk

@roblox/globaltype/File.Size: The size of the file on disk, in bytes
@roblox/globaltype/File.GetBinaryContent: A raw binary string representation of the File|File's contents

@roblox/globaltype/File.GetBinaryContent.documentation: Reads the contents of the File as a string

@roblox/globaltype/FileMesh.MeshId: The MeshId is the content ID of the mesh that is to be displayed.
@roblox/globaltype/FileMesh.TextureId: The TextureId is the content ID of the texture that is to be applied to the mesh.

@roblox/globaltype/Fire.SecondaryColor: Determines the color of the of the secondary (inner) flame particles
@roblox/globaltype/Fire.Size: Determines the size of the flame particles

@roblox/globaltype/FlagStand.FlagCapture.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a player bearing an opposing flag, and having the same Player.TeamColor as the stand, touches the FlagStand.

@roblox/globaltype/FloorWire.StudsBetwee: The number of studs between each FloorWire segment.

@roblox/globaltype/FloorWire.TextureSize: Sets the size of the texture used with the FloorWire.
@roblox/globaltype/FloorWire.To: The object that the FloorWire travels to.
@roblox/globaltype/FloorWire.Velocity: The speed that the textures flow along the wire.

@roblox/globaltype/FlyweightService.documentation: Internal service with no functionality available to developers.

@roblox/globaltype/ForceField.Visible: Determines whether or not the ForceField's particle effect is visible.

@roblox/globaltype/FormFactorPart.documentation: The FormFactorPart class is an abstract class. It inherits from the BasePart class and adds the FormFactor property to classes that inherit from it.

@roblox/globaltype/Frame.Style: Sets what the frame looks like from a selection of pre-determined styles.

@roblox/globaltype/GamePassService.Playe: The Asset ID of the game pass. This is not the Game Pass ID (see above)

@roblox/globaltype/GamePassService.Playe.documentation: Returns true if the Player has the specified legacy game pass. Does not work with new game passes

@roblox/globaltype/GameSettings.Addition:
Used internally by Roblox to add additional CoreScript loading directorie.

The value of this string should be full paths to each directory, separated only by semicolons (;)
@roblox/globaltype/GameSettings.Override: Describes a path to a .lua file that will be ran in place of the default StarterScript.
@roblox/globaltype/GameSettings.VideoCap: Toggles whether or not video capture is enabled.

@roblox/globaltype/GenericSettings.documentation: The abstract class for settings database classes.

@roblox/globaltype/Geometry.documentation: An internal Roblox service which cannot be used by developers.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.documentation: An object that exposes methods to access a single data store

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.GetAs: The key name for which the value is requested. If DataStoreOptions.AllScopes was set to true when accessing the data store through DataStoreService:GetDataStore, this key name must be prepended with the original scope as in "scope/key".

The value of the entry in the data store with the given key and a DataStoreKeyInfo instance that includes the version number, date and time the version was created, and functions to retrieve Player.UserId and metadata.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.GetAs.documentation: Returns the value of a key in a specified data store and a DataStoreKeyInfo instance.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.Incre: Key name for which the value should be updated. If DataStoreOptions.AllScopes was set to true when accessing the data store through DataStoreService:GetDataStore, this key name must be prepended with the original scope as in "scope/key".
Amount to increment the current value by.
(Optional) A table of Player.UserId to associate with the key.
(Optional) DataStoreIncrementOptions instance that combines multiple additional parameters as custom metadata and allows for future extensibility.
The updated value of the entry in the data store with the given key.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.Incre.documentation: Increments the value of a key by the provided amount (both must be integers).

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.Remov: Key name to be removed. If DataStoreOptions.AllScopes was set to true when accessing the data store through DataStoreService:GetDataStore, this key name must be prepended with the original scope as in "scope/key".

The value of the data store prior to deletion and a DataStoreKeyInfo instance that includes the version number, date and time the version was created, and functions to retrieve Player.UserId and metadata.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.Remov.documentation: Removes the specified key while also retaining an accessible version.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.SetAs: Key name for which the value should be set. If DataStoreOptions.AllScopes was set to true when accessing the data store through DataStoreService:GetDataStore, this key name must be prepended with the original scope as in "scope/key".
The value that the data store key will be set to.
Table of Player.UserId, highly recommended to assist with GDPR tracking/removal.
(Optional) DataStoreSetOptions instance that allows for metadata specification on the key.

The version identifier of the newly created version. It can be used to retrieve key info using DataStore/GetVersionAsync|GetVersionAsync() or to remove it using DataStore/RemoveVersionAsync|RemoveVersionAsync().

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.SetAs.documentation: Sets the value of the data store for the given key.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.Updat: Key name for which the value should be updated. If DataStoreOptions.AllScopes was set to true when accessing the data store through DataStoreService:GetDataStore, this key name must be prepended with the original scope as in "scope/key".
Transform function that takes the current value and DataStoreKeyInfo as parameters and returns the new value along with optional Player.UserId and metadata.

The updated value of the entry in the data store with the given key and a DataStoreKeyInfo instance that includes the version number, date and time the version was created, and functions to retrieve Player.UserId and metadata.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.Updat.documentation: Updates a key's value with a new value from the specified callback function.

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.OnUpd: The key identifying the entry being retrieved from the data store
The function to be executed any time the value associated with key is changed
The connection to the key being tracked for updates

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalDataStore.OnUpd.documentation: Sets callback as a function to be executed any time the value associated with key is changed

@roblox/globaltype/GlobalSettings.GetFFl.documentation: Returns the value of an FFlag if it exists.

@roblox/globaltype/GuiRoot.documentation: GuiRoot is an internal service that is used to store Roblox's legacy native UI system. It is still used for some of the stats panels, hence why it is still around today.

@roblox/globaltype/GuiService.documentation:
The GuiService is a service which currently allows developers to control what GuiObject is currently being selected by the gamepad navigator. It also allows clients to check if Roblox's main menu is currently open.

This service has a lot of hidden members, which are mainly used internally by Roblox's CoreScript.

@roblox/globaltype/GuiService.AutoSelect: If the select button on a gamepad will automatically set a GUI as the selected object when the Select button is pressed. Turning this off will mean that Gui navigation will still work if GuiNavigationEnabled is enabled but you will have to set SelectedObject manually to start Gui navigation.

@roblox/globaltype/GuiService.IsWindows: Indicates whether the user is playing on a computer running Windows.

@roblox/globaltype/GuiService.AddSelecti.documentation: Creates a gui selection group where gamepad gui navigation will only consider selectable gui objects that are within the group (children of selectionParent).

AddSelectionTuple works similarly to GuiService:AddSelectionParent, but you can give it a tuple of GuiObject that you want to be contained in the group.

Beware that the second argument is not a table, but rather the first of several GuiObject in the tuple. To pass the contents of a table, use unpack/table.unpack:

local frame = script.Parent
-- Passing various GuiObject individually
GuiService:AddSelectionTuple("InventoryButtons", frame.Sort, frame.Trash, frame.Drop)
-- Unpacking a table of GuiObject (unpack/table.unpack are equivalent)
local inventoryButtons = { frame.Sort, frame.Trash, frame.Drop }
GuiService:AddSelectionTuple("InventoryButtons", unpack(inventoryButtons))

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.AutoJumpEnab: Sets whether the character will automatically jump when they hit an obstacle as a player on a mobile device.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.AutoRotate: AutoRotate sets whether or not the Humanoid will automatically rotate to face in the direction they are moving in.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.BreakJointsO: Determines whether a Humanoid|Humanoid's joints break when in the Dead state
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.CameraOffset: An offset applied to the Camera's subject position when its CameraSubject is set to this Humanoid.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.DisplayDista: Controls the distance behavior of the Humanoid's name and health display.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.DisplayName: Sets the text of a Humanoid, displayed above their head.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.FloorMateria: Describes the Enum.Material that the Humanoid is currently standing on. If the Humanoid isn't standing on anything, the value of this property will be Air.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.Health: Describes the current health of the Humanoid on the range [0, Humanoid.MaxHealth].
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.HealthDispla: Used in conjunction with the Humanoid's Humanoid.DisplayDistanceType property to either determine how far a player controlling this Humanoid can see another humanoid's health bar, or how far this Humanoid's health displays to other viewing players.
Controls when the Humanoid|Humanoid's health bar is allowed to be displayed.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.HipHeight: Determines the distance off the ground the Humanoid.RootPart should be.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.Jump: Whether the Humanoid is jumping. If set to true, it will cause the Humanoid to jump.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.JumpHeight: Provides control over the force with which a Humanoid jumps
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.JumpPower: Determines how much upwards force is applied to the Humanoid when jumping
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.MaxSlopeAngl: The maximum slope angle that a humanoid can walk on without slipping
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.MoveDirectio: Describes the direction that the Humanoid is walking in, as a unit vector along the X/Z axis.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.NameDisplayD: Used in conjunction with the Humanoid's DisplayDistanceType property to either determine how far a player controlling this Humanoid can see another humanoid's name, or how far this Humanoid's name displays to other viewing players.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.NameOcclusio: Controls whether a Humanoid|Humanoid's name can be seen behind walls or other objects.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.PlatformStan: Determines whether the Humanoid is currently in the PlatformStanding Enum.HumanoidStateType.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.RequiresNeck: Allows developers to disable the behavior where a player Character dies if the Neck Motor6D is removed or disconnected even momentarily
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.RigType: Describes whether this Humanoid is utilizing the legacy R6 character rig, or the new R15 character rig.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.SeatPart: A reference to the seat that a Humanoid is currently sitting in, if any.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.TargetPoint: Describes the 3D position where the Player controlling the Humanoid last clicked in the world while using a Tool
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.UseJumpPower: Determines whether the StarterPlayer.CharacterJumpHeight (false) or StarterPlayer.CharacterJumpPower (true) property is used
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.WalkSpeed: Describes the Humanoid|Humanoid's maximum movement speed in studs/sec
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.WalkToPart: A reference to a part whose position is trying to be reached by a humanoid.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.WalkToPoint: The position that a humanoid is trying to reach, after a call to Humanoid:MoveTo is made.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.CollisionTyp: Selects the Enum.HumanoidCollisionType for R15 and Rthro non-player characters
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.LeftLeg: A reference to the humanoid's Left Leg part.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.RightLeg: A reference to the humanoid's Right Leg part.
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.Torso: A reference to a humanoid's root driving part.

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.BuildRigFrom.documentation: Assembles a tree of Motor6D joints by attaching together Attachment objects in a Humanoid|Humanoid's character

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.GetAccessori: An array of Accessory that are parented to the Humanoid|Humanoid's parent

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.GetAccessori.documentation: Returns an array of Accessory that the Humanoid|Humanoid’s parent is currently wearing

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.GetAppliedDe.documentation: Returns back a copy of the Humanoid|Humanoid's cached HumanoidDescription, which describes its current look

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.GetBodyPartR: The specified part being checked to see if it is an R15 body part
The specified part's R15 body part type or unknown if the part is not a body part
@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.GetLimb/para: The Part for which the Enum/Limb|Enum.Limb is to be retrieved

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.GetLimb.documentation: Returns the Enum.Limb enum that is associated with the given Part

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.GetStateEnab.documentation: Returns whether a Enum.HumanoidStateType is enabled for the Humanoid

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.Move/param/1: True if the direction parameter should be taken as relative to the Workspace.CurrentCamera

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.Move.documentation: Causes the Humanoid to walk in the given direction

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.MoveTo.documentation: Causes the Humanoid to attempt to walk to the given location by setting the Humanoid.WalkToPoint and Humanoid.WalkToPart properties

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.ReplaceBodyP.documentation: Dynamically replaces a Humanoid body part with a different part.

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.SetStateEnab: True if this state is to be enabled, false if it is to be disabled

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.SetStateEnab.documentation: Sets whether a given Enum.HumanoidStateType is enabled for the Humanoid

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.TakeDamage/p: The damage, or amount to be deduced from the Humanoid.Health

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.TakeDamage.documentation: Lowers the Humanoid.Health of the Humanoid by the given amount if it is not protected by a ForceField

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.ApplyDescrip: The HumanoidDescription Instance which you want to set the character to match

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.ApplyDescrip.documentation: Makes the Player/Character|character's look match that of the passed in HumanoidDescription

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.HasStatus.documentation: Returns a boolean based on if a status exists.

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.RemoveCustom.documentation: Removes the defined custom status from the Status model in the Humanoid..

@roblox/globaltype/Humanoid.RemoveStatus.documentation: .Removes the defined status from the Status model in the Humanoid.

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.A: A JSON formatted array of Layered Accessorys where each table in the entry in the array describes an accessory’s AssetId, AccessoryType, Order, and (optionally) Puffiness as key-value pairs.
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.B: A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to its back (such as capes)

Determines the factor by which the shape of a Humanoid rig is interpolated from the standard R15 body shape (0) to a taller and more slender body type (1); when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, maps to the "BodyTypeScale" NumberValue within the HumanoidDescription
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.C: When this description is Humanoid:ApplyDescription to a Humanoid, this determines the Animation.AnimationId to play when its Humanoid:GetState is enum.HumanoidStateType
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.D: Determines by what factor the depth (back-to-front distance) of a Humanoid rig is scaled; when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, maps to the "DepthScale" NumberValue within the Humanoid
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.F: Determines the asset ID of the Face to be applied to the Humanoid
A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to the front of its face (such as glasses)
When this description is Humanoid:ApplyDescription to a Humanoid, this determines the Animation.AnimationId to play when its Humanoid:GetState is enum.HumanoidStateType
A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to front of its torso (such as medals or ties)
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.H: A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to its head resembling hair
A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to its head
Determines the asset ID of the Head to be applied to the Humanoid
Determines by what factor the Head of a Humanoid is scaled; when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, maps to the "HeadScale" NumberValue within the Humanoid
Determines by what factor the height (top-to-bottom distance) of a Humanoid rig is scaled; when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, maps to the "HeightScale" NumberValue within the Humanoid
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.I: When this description is Humanoid:ApplyDescription to a Humanoid, this determines the Animation.AnimationId to play when its Humanoid:GetState is enum.HumanoidStateType at a speed near zero
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.J: When this description is Humanoid:ApplyDescription to a Humanoid, this determines the Animation.AnimationId to play when its Humanoid:GetState is enum.HumanoidStateType
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.L: Determines the asset ID of the LeftArm to be applied to the Humanoid
Determines the asset ID of the LeftLeg to be applied to the Humanoid
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.N: A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to its neck (such as scarves or necklaces)
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.P: Determines how wide (0) or narrow (1) a Humanoid rig is; when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, maps to the "BodyProportionScale" NumberValue within the Humanoid.
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.R: Determines the asset ID of the RightArm to be applied to the Humanoid
Determines the BodyColors.RightArmColor3 of a Humanoid when applied
Determines the asset ID of the RightLeg to be applied to the Humanoid
Determines the BodyColors.RightLegColor3 of a Humanoid when applied
When this description is Humanoid:ApplyDescription to a Humanoid, this determines the Animation.AnimationId to play when its Humanoid:GetState is enum.HumanoidStateType at a moderate speed.
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.S: A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to its shoulders (such as shoulder-mounted critters)
When this description is Humanoid:ApplyDescription to a Humanoid, this determines the Animation.AnimationId to play when its Humanoid:GetState is enum.HumanoidStateType
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.T: Determines the asset ID of the Torso to be applied to the Humanoid
Determines the BodyColors.TorsoColor3 of a Humanoid when applied
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.W: A comma-separated list of asset IDs that will be added as Accessory to a Humanoid rig when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, usually those attached to its waist (such as belts)
When this description is Humanoid:ApplyDescription to a Humanoid, this determines the Animation.AnimationId to play when its Humanoid:GetState is enum.HumanoidStateType at a low speed
Determines by what factor the width (left-to-right distance) of a Humanoid is scaled; when Humanoid:ApplyDescription, maps to the "BodyWidthScale" NumberValue within the Humanoid
@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.A: A string that identifies what emote is being added. Example: "Salute"
An emote asset ID (see Featured emotes in the Catalog). Example: 3360689775 (Salute)

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.A.documentation: Adds the emote to the description given a name and its asset ID

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.G.documentation: Returns a table of an avatar’s current accessories.

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.G:
A dictionary of emotes where the key is the emote name and the value is an array of emote asset IDs. Example:

{
    Salute = {3360689775},
    Agree = {4849487550},
    Disagree = {4849495710}
}

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.G.documentation: Returns a dictionary of emotes that have been HumanoidDescription:AddEmote or HumanoidDescription:SetEmotes to this description

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.G:
An array of tables describing the name and slot which each emote is equipped. Example:

{
    {Slot = 3, Name = "Salute"},
    {Slot = 2, Name = "Agree"},
    {Slot = 1, Name = "Disagree"},
}

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.G.documentation: Returns an array of tables describing the equipped emotes that have been HumanoidDescription:SetEquippedEmotes

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.R: The name of the emote as it was HumanoidDescription:SetEmotes or HumanoidDescription:AddEmote

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.R.documentation: Removes any emotes that have been added under the given name

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.S.documentation: Accepts a table that sets the accessories and related properties for an avatar.

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.S:
A dictionary of emotes where the key is the emote name and the value is an array of emote asset IDs. Example:

{
    Salute = {3360689775},
    Agree = {4849487550},
    Disagree = {4849495710}
}

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.S.documentation: Sets all of the emotes on this description

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.S:
An array of emote names. Example:

{ "Disagree", "Agree", "Salute" }

– OR – An array of tables describing the name and slot which each emote is equipped. Example:

{
    {Slot = 3, Name = "Salute"},
    {Slot = 2, Name = "Agree"},
    {Slot = 1, Name = "Disagree"},
}

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.S.documentation: Sets the currently equipped emotes given an array of emote names

@roblox/globaltype/HumanoidDescription.E.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when emotes are added, removed or set on this description
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Light.Shadows: If set to true, will project shadows if light is blocked by an obstacle.

@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.documentation: The Lighting service controls the environmental lighting in a game. It includes a range of adjustable properties that can be used to change how lighting appears and interacts with other objects.

@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.Ambient: The lighting hue applied to areas that are occluded from the sky, such as indoor areas
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.Brightness: The intensity of illumination in the place.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.ClockTime: A numerical representation (in hours) of the current time of day used by Lighting.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.ColorShift_B: The hue represented in light reflected in the opposite surfaces to those facing the sun or moon.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.ColorShift_T: The hue represented in light reflected from surfaces facing the sun or moon.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.EnvironmentD: Ambient light that is derived from the environment
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.FogColor: A DataType.Color3 value giving the hue of Lighting's fog.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.FogEnd: The depth from the Workspace.CurrentCamera, in studs, at which fog will be completely opaque.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.FogStart: The depth from the Workspace.CurrentCamera, in studs, at which fog begins to show.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.GeographicLa: The geographic latitude, in degrees, of the scene, influencing the result of Lightings time on the position of the sun and moon.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.GlobalShadow: Toggles voxel-based dynamic lighting for the game
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.OutdoorAmbie: The lighting hue applied to outdoor areas.

@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.TimeOfDay: A 24 hour string representation of the current time of day used by Lighting.
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.Outlines: Determines whether outlines are enabled or disabled in a place
@roblox/globaltype/Lighting.ShadowColor: This is supposed to change the color of player shadows, but currently doesn't do anything.

@roblox/globaltype/MarketplaceService.Pr:
The receiptInfo is a table with the following keys:

  • PlayerId (number): The user ID of the player that made a purchase
  • PlaceIdWherePurchased (number): The place ID in which a purchase was made
  • PurchaseId (string): A unique identifier for a purchase that ought to be used to prevent granting a product multiple times
  • ProductId (number): The ID number of the purchased product
  • CurrencyType (Enum.CurrencyType): Deprecated. The type of currency used in the transaction.
  • CurrencySpent (number): The amount of currency spent in the transaction.

An enum representing in what manner the developer product receipt was processed:

  • PurchaseGranted indicates that the game successfully granted the player the benefit the developer product is meant to provide, such as a currency boost, gameplay bonus, item, etc. This indicates to Roblox that the sale was performed successfully. Do not return PurchaseGranted if the product could not be granted.
  • NotProcessedYet indicates the developer product's benefit could not be granted, such as a product the player is not eligible to purchase, is no longer relevant to the current game state, etc.
