@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreQueue.documentation: Provides access to a queue within MemoryStore.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreQueue.AddA: The value of the item to add to the queue.
Item expiration time, in seconds, after which the item will be automatically removed from the queue.
Item priority. Items with higher priority are retrieved from the queue before items with lower priority.
@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreQueue.Read: Number of items to read. The maximum allowed value of this parameter is 100.

Controls the behavior of the method in the case the queue has fewer than count items: if set to false the method returns all available items; if set to true, it returns no items. The default value is false.

The duration, in seconds, for which the method will wait if the required number of items is not immediately available in the queue. This parameter can be set to zero to indicate no wait. If this parameter is not provided or set to -1, the method will wait indefinitely.

A tuple of two elements. The first element is an array of item values read from the queue. The second element is a string identifier that should be passed to MemoryStoreQueue:RemoveAsync to permanently remove these items from the queue.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreQueue.Read.documentation: Reads one or more items from the queue.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreQueue.Remo: Identifies the items to delete. Use the value returned by MemoryStoreQueue:ReadAsync.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreQueue.Remo.documentation: Removes an item or items previously read from the queue.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreService.documentation: Exposes methods to access specific primitives within MemoryStore.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreService.Ge: (Optional) Invisibility timeout, in seconds, for read operations through this queue instance. If not provided, defaults to 30 seconds.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreService.Ge.documentation: Returns a MemoryStoreQueue instance for the provided name.
Returns a MemoryStoreSortedMap instance for the provided name.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreSortedMap.documentation: Provides access to a sorted map within MemoryStore.

Key value, or nil -- if there’s no item with the specified key.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreSortedMap..documentation: Retrieves the value of a key in the sorted map.

The number of items to retrieve; the maximum allowed value for this parameter is 200.
(Optional) Lower bound, exclusive, for the returned keys.
(Optional) Upper bound, exclusive, for the returned keys.
Item keys and values in the requested range.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreSortedMap..documentation: Retrieves items within a sorted range of keys.
Removes the provided key from the sorted map.

Item expiration, in seconds. The item is automatically removed from the sorted map once the expiration duration is reached. The maximum expiration time is 30 days (2,592,000 seconds).
True if a new item was added, false -- if an existing item was updated.
A function which you need to provide. The function takes the key’s old value as input and returns the new value.
Item expiration time, in seconds, after which the item will be automatically removed from the sorted map. The maximum expiration time is 30 days (2,592,000 seconds).
The return value is the last value returned by the transform function.

@roblox/globaltype/MemoryStoreSortedMap..documentation: Retrieves the value of a key from a sorted map and updates it with a new value.

@roblox/globaltype/MeshContentProvider.documentation: An internal Roblox service that is responsible for fetching, parsing and caching meshes. This service cannot be used by developers.

@roblox/globaltype/MeshPart.documentation: A form of BasePart that includes a physically simulated custom mesh.

@roblox/globaltype/MeshPart.DoubleSided: Render both faces of polygons in the mesh
@roblox/globaltype/MeshPart.MeshId: The MeshId is the content ID of the mesh that is to be displayed on the MeshPart
@roblox/globaltype/MeshPart.RenderFideli: Determines the level of detail that solid-modeled and mesh parts will be shown in
@roblox/globaltype/MeshPart.MeshID: The MeshId is the content ID of the mesh that is to be displayed on the MeshPart

@roblox/globaltype/Message.documentation: Fills the entire screen with a semi-transparent grey background, with centered text in the middle of the screen. With the introduction of Roblox's GUI features it has been deprecated and TextLabels should be used instead for new work.

@roblox/globaltype/MessagingService.documentation: MessagingService allows game servers in the same game to communicate with each other

@roblox/globaltype/MessagingService.Publ: The data to include in the message

@roblox/globaltype/MessagingService.Publ.documentation: Invokes the supplied callback whenever a message is pushed to the topic

@roblox/globaltype/MessagingService.Subs: Function to be invoked whenever a message is received
Connection that can be used to unsubscribe from the topic

@roblox/globaltype/Model.documentation: Models are container objects, meaning they group objects together. They are best used to hold collections of BasePart and have a number of functions that extend their functionality.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.PrimaryPart: Points to the primary part of the Model.
@roblox/globaltype/Model.World Pivot Ori: Editor-only property to set the orientation of the pivot. Scripts must use Model.WorldPivot instead.
@roblox/globaltype/Model.World Pivot Pos: Editor-only property to set the position of the pivot. Scripts must use Model.WorldPivot instead.
@roblox/globaltype/Model.WorldPivot: Determines where the pivot of a Model which does not have a set Model.PrimaryPart is located.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.BreakJoints.documentation: Breaks connections between BaseParts, including surface connections with any adjacent parts, WeldConstraints and all Welds and other JointInstances.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.GetBoundingBox/: A DataType.CFrame representing the orientation of the volume followed by a DataType.Vector3 representing the size of the volume

@roblox/globaltype/Model.GetBoundingBox.documentation: Returns a description of a volume that contains all parts of a Model

@roblox/globaltype/Model.GetExtentsSize.documentation: Returns the size of the smallest bounding box that contains all of the BaseParts in the Model, aligned with the Model.PrimaryPart if it is set.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.GetPrimaryPartC.documentation: Returns the CFrame of the Model's Model.PrimaryPart. This function will throw an error if no primary part exists for the Model.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.MakeJoints.documentation: Goes through all BaseParts in the Model. If any part's side has a SurfaceType that can make a joint it will create a joint with any adjacent parts

@roblox/globaltype/Model.MoveTo/param/0: The DataType.Position the Model is to be moved to.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.MoveTo.documentation: Moves the Model.PrimaryPart to the given position. If a primary part has not been specified then the root part of the model will be used.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.SetPrimaryPartC.documentation: Sets the BasePart.CFrame of the Model's Model.PrimaryPart. All other parts in the model will also be moved and will maintain their orientation and offset respective to the Model.PrimaryPart.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.TranslateBy.documentation: Shifts a Model by the given Vector3 offset, preserving the Model's orientation. If another BasePart or Terrain already exists at the new position then the Model will overlap said object.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.GetModelCFrame.documentation: This value historically returned the CFrame of a central position in the model. It has been deprecated as it did not provide reliable results.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.GetModelSize.documentation: Returns the Vector3 size of the Model.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.ResetOrientatio.documentation: Resets the rotation of the model's parts to the previously set identity rotation, which is done through the Model:SetIdentityOrientation method.

@roblox/globaltype/Model.SetIdentityOrie.documentation: Sets the identity rotation of the given model, allowing you to reset the rotation of the entire model later, through the use of the ResetOrientationToIdentity method.

@roblox/globaltype/ModuleScript.documentation: A type of script object that runs once when require is called with it. Returns exactly one value, usually a table of functions, to used by other scripts. Useful for compartmentalizing code.

@roblox/globaltype/ModuleScript.LinkedSo: Used to store a URL that points to an online script source. Binds the online code to the script's Script.Source
@roblox/globaltype/Motor.CurrentAngle: Displays the current rotation of the motor in radians.
@roblox/globaltype/Motor.DesiredAngle: The desired angle to turn the motor to in radians.
@roblox/globaltype/Motor.MaxVelocity: The maximum velocity the motor can use to reach Motor.DesiredAngle measured in radians per physics frame (1/60th of a second).
@roblox/globaltype/Motor6D.Transform: Describes the current animation offset of the Motor6D joint

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.documentation: Legacy object that contains members useful for pointer input

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Hit: The DataType.CFrame of the mouse's position in 3D space
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Icon: The content ID of the image used as the Mouse's icon.
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Origin: A DataType.CFrame positioned at the Workspace.CurrentCamera and oriented toward the Mouse's 3D position.
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Target: The object in 3D space the Mouse is pointing to
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.TargetFilter: Determines an object (and its descendants) to be ignored when determining Mouse.Hit and Mouse.Target
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.TargetSurface: Indicates the Enum.NormalId of the BasePart surface at which the mouse is pointing
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.UnitRay: A DataType.Ray directed towards the Mouse's world position, originating from the Workspace.CurrentCamera's world position
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.ViewSizeX: Describes the width of the game window in pixels
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.ViewSizeY: Describes the height of the game window in pixels
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.X: Describes the X (horizontal) component of the mouse's position on the screen
@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Y: Describes the Y (vertical) component of the mouse’s screen position

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button1Down.Con.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button1Down.Wai.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button1Down.documentation: Fired when the left mouse button is pressed.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button1Up.Conne.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button1Up.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button1Up.documentation: Fires when the left mouse button is released.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button2Down.Con.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button2Down.Wai.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button2Down.documentation: Fires when the right mouse button is pressed.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button2Up.Conne.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button2Up.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Button2Up.documentation: Fired when the right mouse button is released

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Idle.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Idle.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Idle.documentation: Fired during every heartbeat that the mouse isn't being passed to another mouse event.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Move.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.Move.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.WheelBackward.C.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.WheelBackward.W.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.WheelBackward.documentation: Fires when the mouse wheel is scrolled backwards

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.WheelForward.Co.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.WheelForward.Wa.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.WheelForward.documentation: Fires when the mouse wheel is scrolled forwards.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.KeyDown.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.KeyDown.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.KeyUp.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.KeyUp.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.keyDown.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Mouse.keyDown.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/NegateOperation.documentation: Creates a CSG part that can be removed from other part via solid modeling

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkClient.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the client successfully connects to a server. Returns a string showing the server's IP and Port, and the client's ClientReplicator.
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired if the client fails to connect to the server.

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkMarker.documentation: The NetworkMarker is used to tell the client when the server has finished loading the world for the client.

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkMarker.Receive.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the server has finished replicating the world to the client.

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkPeer.documentation: The NetworkPeer object is the most basic class of the network objects.

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkPeer.SetOutgoi.documentation: Sets the maximum outgoing bandwidth that Roblox can use.

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkReplicator.documentation: An object which handles the replication of other objects either from the server to the client, or from the client to the server.

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkReplicator.Get.documentation: Returns the player that is connected to the NetworkReplicator.

@roblox/globaltype/NetworkSettings.FreeM: Describes how much free memory is available, in MBs.
@roblox/globaltype/NetworkSettings.Print: When set to true, debug messages will be printed into the output pertaining to physics replication errors.
When set to true, debug information is printed to the output regarding the replication of instances when Workspace.StreamingEnabled is set to true.
@roblox/globaltype/NetworkSettings.Rende: When set to true, regions of space that are being streamed to the client will be outlined in red.
@roblox/globaltype/NetworkSettings.ShowA: When set to true, a label will be shown above each Player's head, showing the current animation being played by the Player's Humanoid, if any.
@roblox/globaltype/NetworkSettings.Track: When set to true, the replicator stats will sample data about packets that are being sent.
When set to true, this tells the replicator stats to sample replication physics details.

@roblox/globaltype/NoCollisionConstraint.documentation: An instance used to prevent collisions between two specific parts

@roblox/globaltype/NoCollisionConstraint: Determines whether the two constrained parts will collide with each other

@roblox/globaltype/NonReplicatedCSGDicti.documentation: A version of the CSGDictionaryService that does not replicate to clients.

@roblox/globaltype/NotificationService.documentation: An internal service which cannot be used by developers.

@roblox/globaltype/NotificationService.R.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/NumberValue.documentation: A container object for a single double-precision floating point number.

@roblox/globaltype/NumberValue.Changed.C.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/NumberValue.Changed.W.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/NumberValue.changed.C.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/NumberValue.changed.W.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/ObjectValue.documentation: A container object for a reference to another instance.

@roblox/globaltype/ObjectValue.Changed.C.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/ObjectValue.Changed.W.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/ObjectValue.changed.C.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/ObjectValue.changed.W.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/OrderedDataStore.documentation: A GlobalDataStore that also allows for ordered data store entries

@roblox/globaltype/OrderedDataStore.GetS: A boolean indicating whether the returned data pages are in ascending order.
Optional parameter. If set, data pages with a value less than than minValue will be excluded.
Optional parameter. If set, data pages with a value greater than maxValue will be excluded.
A sorted DataStorePages object based on the provided arguments.

@roblox/globaltype/PackageLink.documentation: Links a DataModel instance to a corresponding asset in the cloud

@roblox/globaltype/PackageLink.AutoUpdat: When this property is set to true, the package associated with the given PackageLink will be automatically updated to the latest version
@roblox/globaltype/PackageLink.PackageId: The id of the asset this package corresponds to
@roblox/globaltype/PackageLink.VersionNu: Refers to a revision of a specific package
@roblox/globaltype/Pages.IsFinished: Whether or not the current page is the last page available.

@roblox/globaltype/Pages.GetCurrentPage.documentation: Returns the items on the current page. The keys in the item are determined by the source of this object.

@roblox/globaltype/Pages.AdvanceToNextPa.documentation: Iterates to the next page in the pages object, if possible.

@roblox/globaltype/Pants.documentation: Displays a Pants texture from the Roblox website to display on a Humanoid rig

@roblox/globaltype/Pants.PantsTemplate: Determines the texture of the Pants. The content ID link pointing to the pants template hosted on the Roblox website.

@roblox/globaltype/Part.documentation: The Part object is a physical object, commonly known as a brick

@roblox/globaltype/Part.Shape: Sets the type of shape the object has.

@roblox/globaltype/PartAdornment.documentation: An abstract class for GUI elements that are adorned to (displayed as attached to) objects deriving from BasePart.

@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.documentation: A special effects object that emits customizable 2D billboard particles into the world

@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Accel: Determines the global-axis acceleration of all alive particles, measured in studs per second squared
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Color: Determines the color of all particles emit over their individual lifetimes
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Drag: Determines the rate at which particles will lose half their speed through exponential decay
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Emiss: Determines the face towards which particles will be emit
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Enabl: Determines whether particles ought to be emit
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Lifet: Defines a random range of ages for newly emit particles
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Light: Determines how much particles' colors are blended with the colors behind them
Determines how much particles are influenced by the the environment light
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Locke: Determines whether the particles rigidly move with the part they're being emitted from.
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Rate: Determines the number of particles emit per second
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.RotSp: Determines the range of angular speeds emitted particles, measured in degrees per second
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Rotat: Determines the range of rotations in degrees for a newly emit particles
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Size: Determines the world size over individual particles' lifetimes
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Speed: Determines the random range of speeds a new particle will have when emit, measured in studs per second
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Sprea: Determines the angles at which particles may be randomly emit, measured in degrees
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Textu: Determines the image rendered on particle billboards
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Trans: Determines the transparency of particles over their individual lifetimes
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Veloc: Determines how much of the parent's velocity is inherited by particles when emitted
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.ZOffs: Determines the forward-backward render position of particles; used to control what particles render on top/bottom
@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Veloc: Determines how offset a particle can be fired from the local emitter direction of its parent

@roblox/globaltype/ParticleEmitter.Clear.documentation: Clears all particles that have been emit

@roblox/globaltype/PartOperation.documentation: An abstract class that all parts based on solid modeling inherit from.

@roblox/globaltype/PartOperation.Smoothi: An angle in degrees which affects the smooth shading of a solid modeled part.
@roblox/globaltype/PartOperation.Triangl: The number of polygons in this solid model. This value will always be <= 5000.
@roblox/globaltype/PartOperation.UsePart: Sets whether the PartOperation can be recolored using the BrickColor property.

@roblox/globaltype/PartOperationAsset.documentation: An internal service which cannot be used by developers.

@roblox/globaltype/Path.documentation: Stores the result of paths created by PathfindingService:CreatePath

@roblox/globaltype/Path.GetWaypoints/ret: An array of DataType.PathWaypoint ordered from path start to path end

@roblox/globaltype/Path.GetWaypoints.documentation: Returns an array of points in the path.

@roblox/globaltype/Path.CheckOcclusionAs.documentation: Checks if a path is blocked starting at a specific waypoint

@roblox/globaltype/Path.ComputeAsync/par: The world position where the computed path begins
The world position where the computed path finishes

@roblox/globaltype/Path.ComputeAsync.documentation: Computes a Path from a start position to an end position

@roblox/globaltype/Path.Blocked.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Path.Blocked.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Path.Unblocked.Connec.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Path.Unblocked.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingModifier.documentation: Modifiers used to represent space that has a higher or lower cost to be traversed when creating paths using the PathfindingService

@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingModifier.M: The name of the navigation area inside or on top of the Part|Part's volume
@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingModifier.P: Determines if the parts enclosed by the modifier are traversable, even if they would normally be collided with.

@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingService.documentation: Used to find paths between two points

@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingService.Em: Sets the percent of a voxel has to be occupied to be considered empty. Defaults to 0.16.
@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingService.Cr: Lua table which lets you fine-tune the path for the size of the agent (the humanoid that will move along the path). See Agent Parameters.

@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingService.Fi.documentation: Finds a Path between the two provided points

@roblox/globaltype/PathfindingService.Co.documentation: Computes and returns a Path between two DataType.Vector3. If the given MaxDistance is greater than 512, an error will be thrown. (MaxDistance is too large).
Computes and returns a smooth Path between two DataType.Vector3

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsPacketCache.documentation: An internal service, used for physics networking. This service is not accessible to developers.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.Collis.documentation: Returns whether the part is in the collision group.
Sets the collision status between two groups.
Returns whether the two groups will collide.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.Create.documentation: Creates a new collision group with the given name, and returns the id of the created group.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.GetCol: The name of the collision group being retrieved.
The id of the retrieved collision group, or nil if no such group exists.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.GetCol.documentation: Returns the id of the group with the specified name.
Returns the name of the group with the corresponding id.
Returns a table with info on all of the place's collision groups.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.GetMax.documentation: Returns the maximum number of collision groups.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.Remove.documentation: Removes the collision group with the given name.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.SetPar: The name of collision group that the part's collision group is being set to.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsService.SetPar.documentation: Sets the collision group of a part.

@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.Allow: When set to true, physically simulated objects will stop being simulated if they have little to no motion for a set period of time.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreAn: When set to true, parts that are BasePart.Anchored will show a gray surface outline on the surface of the part's bounding box that is currently facing the ground.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreAs: When set to true, each physics assembly is assigned a unique color and the Part associated with the assembly are outlined with the color. Parts that are attached together by JointInstance will share the same color.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreAw: When set to true, parts that are actively being physically simulated will have a red outline.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreBo: When set to true, Part will be outlined with a specific color, depending on the state of its root simulation body.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreCo: When set to true, each contact island will render SelectionBox adorns on the parts in contact islands, where each contact island is assigned a random color.
When set to true, sphere adorns will be drawn at the contact points of each part where physics interactions are occurring.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreJo: When set to true, XYZ axes are rendered at the BasePart.CFrame of every part.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreMe: When set to true, every individual mechanism of parts is given a unique color.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreMo: An ancient property that hasn't work correctly since late 2007. It's supposed to render an XYZ axis on the root part of a Model, but the axis rendering component doesn't work correctly.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreOw: When set to true, each Player's character is outlined with a unique color, and each part that the player has network ownership over is outlined with the same color.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.ArePa: An ancient property that hasn't worked correctly since late 2007. It's supposed to render a large XYZ axis in the center of each BasePart, but the axis rendering component doesn't work correctly.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreRe: When set to true, a cylinder is drawn around each Player's character, representing their Player.SimulationRadius.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreUn: When set to true, parts that aren't aligned on the 1x1x1 grid will be outlined yellow.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.AreWo: An ancient property that hasn't worked correctly since late 2007. It's supposed to render a large XYZ axis in the center of the world, but the axis rendering component doesn't work correctly.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.Disab: When set to true, Roblox will fall back to using its legacy CSG solver when performing solid model operations.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.IsRec: This property is supposed to show the BasePart.ReceiveAge of a part, but it does not work correctly.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.IsTre: When set to true, the joint connections of each part, and the states of their underlying primitive components are visualized as a spanning tree.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.Physi: Controls the throttle rate of Roblox's physics engine.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.ShowD: When set to true, the underlying collision geometry for PartOperation and MeshPart is rendered.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.Throt: If the PhysicsSettings.PhysicsEnvironmentalThrottle is set to DefaultAuto, this specifies the maximum time that the physics environmental throttle has to wait before it is allowed to automatically change.
@roblox/globaltype/PhysicsSettings.UseCS: If set to true, version 2 of Roblox's CSG solver will be used instead of version 1.
@roblox/globaltype/PitchShiftSoundEffect: The percentage to shift the original pitch.

@roblox/globaltype/Platform.documentation: Historically a form of Seat that wouldn't place the player in a sitting pose. This object is no longer create-able and cannot be used by developers

@roblox/globaltype/Player.documentation: An object that represents a presently connected client to the game.

@roblox/globaltype/Player.AccountAge: Describes the player's account age in days.
@roblox/globaltype/Player.AutoJumpEnable: Determines whether the character of a player using a mobile device will automatically jump upon hitting an obstacle.
@roblox/globaltype/Player.CameraMaxZoomD: The maximum distance the player's camera is allowed to zoom out.
@roblox/globaltype/Player.CameraMinZoomD: The minimum distance the player's camera is allowed to zoom in.
@roblox/globaltype/Player.CameraMode: Changes the camera's mode to either first or third person.
@roblox/globaltype/Player.CanLoadCharact: Determines whether the character's appearance will be loaded when the player spawns. If false, the player will spawn with a default appearance.

Creates a temporary action that is hidden from Studio's customize shortcuts window

  • This function creates a temporary action that is hidden from Studio's customize shortcuts window.

See also

  • articles/Intro to Plugins, an introductory article to plugin use and development
  • PluginAction, an object that represents a generic performable action in Roblox Studio, with no directly associated Toolbar or Button.
  • Plugin:CreatePluginAction, creates a PluginAction
  • PluginMenu.Title, the text to be displayed when used as a sub menu
  • PluginMenu.Icon, the icon to be displayed when used as a sub menu
  • PluginMenu:AddAction, adds the given action to the menu
  • PluginMenu:AddMenu, adds the given menu as a separator
  • PluginMenu:AddSeparator, adds a separator between items in the menu
  • PluginMenu:Clear, clears the menu
  • PluginMenu:ShowAsync, shows the menu at the mouse cursor. Yields until either an item is selected or the menu is closed. The selected action fires its Triggered event

@roblox/globaltype/RunService.BindToRend: The name parameter is a label for the binding, and can be used with RunService.Unbind if the binding is no longer needed

The priority of the binding is an integer, and determines when during the render step to call the custom function. The lower this number, the sooner the custom function will be called. If two bindings have the same priority the Roblox engine will randomly pick one to run first. The default Roblox control scripts run with these specific priorities: - Player Input: 100 - Camera Controls: 200 For convenience, the '''RenderPriority''' enum can be used to determine the integer value to set a binding. For example, to make a binding right before the default camera update, simply subtract 1 from the camera priority level.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.GetBre.documentation: Returns a list of DebuggerBreakpoint present in the script.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.GetGlo.documentation: Returns a dictionary of all variables that are visible to the script's global stack, where the keys are the names of the variables, and the values are the actual values of the variables.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.GetLoc.documentation: Returns a dictionary of all local variables in the specified stack, where the keys are the names of the variables, and the values are the actual values of the variables.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.GetSta.documentation: Returns an array of all active call stacks in the script.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.GetUpv.documentation: Returns a dictionary of all upvalues present in the stack specified.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.GetWat.documentation: Returns the current value of a variable being watched by a DebuggerWatch.
Returns a list with all the watches for this debugger

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.SetBre.documentation: Sets the specified line of the script as a breakpoint. Returns a DebuggerBreakpoint that you can use to manage the breakpoint.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.SetGlo.documentation: Sets the value of the variable name as value in the script's main stack.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.SetLoc.documentation: Sets the value of the variable name as value in the stack specified.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.SetUpv.documentation: Sets the value of the upvalue name as value in the stack specified.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.Breakp.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a breakpoint is added to the script.
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a breakpoint is removed from the script.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.Encoun.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a breakpoint is encountered by the script.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.Resumi.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the game is resumed after being paused by a breakpoint.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.WatchA.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when an expression watch is added to this script debugger.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptDebugger.WatchR.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when an expression watch is removed from this script debugger.

@roblox/globaltype/ScriptService.documentation: An unimplemented service that has zero functionality, in a similar manner to the LocalWorkspace service.

@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Absolu: The size in pixels of the frame, without the scrollbars.
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Automa: Determines whether ScrollingFrame.CanvasSize is resized based on child content
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Bottom: The Down image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the image on the horizontal scroll bar.
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Canvas: The location within the canvas, in pixels, that should be drawn at the top left of the scroll frame
Determines the size of the area that is scrollable. The UDim2 is calculated using the parent gui's size, similar to the regular Size property on gui objects.
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Elasti: Determines how elastic scrolling behaves for touch input
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Horizo: Indicates the inset behavior of the horizontal scrolling bar.
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.MidIma: The middle image on the vertical scrollbar. The size of this can vary in the y direction, but is always set as ScrollingFrame.ScrollBarThickness in the x direction. This is also used as the middle image on the horizontal scroll bar.
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Scroll: Determines how a rendered scroll bar image will be colorized
Determines the transparency of the rendered scroll bar image
How thick the scroll bar appears. This applies to both the horizontal and vertical scroll bars. If set to 0, no scroll bars are rendered.
Determines the direction scrolling is allowed in this scrolling frame
Determines whether or not scrolling is allowed on the frame. If false, no scroll bars will be rendered.
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.TopIma: The Up image on the vertical scrollbar. The size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the left image on the horizontal scroll bar.
@roblox/globaltype/ScrollingFrame.Vertic: Indicates the inset behavior of the vertical scrolling bar.
Indicates the side that the vertical scrollbar will be located at.

@roblox/globaltype/Seat.documentation: A type of BasePart that characters can 'sit' in. When a character touches an enabled Seat object, it will be attached to the part by a Weld and the default character scripts will play a sitting animation.

@roblox/globaltype/Seat.Disabled: Whether or not the seat is usable. If set to true, the seat will act as a normal part.
@roblox/globaltype/Seat.Occupant: The humanoid that is sitting in the seat

@roblox/globaltype/Seat.Sit.documentation: Forces the character with the specified Humanoid to sit in the Seat.

@roblox/globaltype/Selection.documentation: The Selection service controls the Instances that are selected in Roblox Studio.

@roblox/globaltype/Selection.Get.documentation: Returns an array of currently selected Instances in Roblox Studio.

@roblox/globaltype/Selection.Set/param/0: An array of Instances to set the current selection to.

@roblox/globaltype/Selection.Set.documentation: Sets the currently selected objects in Roblox Studio to Instances in the given array.

@roblox/globaltype/Selection.SelectionCh.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when the Instances selected in Roblox Studio changes.

@roblox/globaltype/SelectionBox.LineThic: Determines the thickness of the boxes outlines, in studs
@roblox/globaltype/SelectionBox.SurfaceC: Determines the color of the box's surfaces
@roblox/globaltype/SelectionBox.SurfaceT: Determines the transparency of the box's surfaces, similar to BasePart.Transparency
@roblox/globaltype/SelectionLasso.Humano: The Humanoid that the Lasso belongs to, and will come from.

@roblox/globaltype/SelectionPartLasso.documentation: An instance used to display a "lasso" between a Humanoid Torso and a BasePart.

@roblox/globaltype/SelectionPartLasso.Pa: Sets the target of the lasso object.
@roblox/globaltype/SelectionPointLasso.P: Sets the Vector3 target of the lasso object.
@roblox/globaltype/SelectionSphere.Surfa: Determines the color of the sphere's surface
Determines the transparency of the sphere's surface, similar to BasePart.Transparency
@roblox/globaltype/ServerScriptService.L: Toggles whether or not the loadstring function can be used by server scripts. Defaults to false.

@roblox/globaltype/ServerStorage.documentation: A container whose contents are only accessible on the server. Objects descending from ServerStorage will not replicate to the client and will not be accessible from LocalScripts.

@roblox/globaltype/ServiceProvider.documentation: A ServiceProvider is an abstract class, which stores, and provides certain singleton classes, depending on what inherited class you are using its members with.

@roblox/globaltype/ServiceProvider.FindS.documentation: Returns the service specified by the given className if it's already created, errors for an invalid name.

@roblox/globaltype/ServiceProvider.GetSe: The class name of the requested service

@roblox/globaltype/ServiceProvider.GetSe.documentation: Returns the service with the requested class name, creating it if it does not exist.

@roblox/globaltype/ServiceProvider.Close.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when the current place is exited.
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired immediately after the ServiceProvider.Close signal is fired.

@roblox/globaltype/ServiceProvider.Servi.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a service is about to be removed.

@roblox/globaltype/Shirt.documentation: Displays a Shirt texture from the Roblox website to display on a Humanoid rig

@roblox/globaltype/Shirt.ShirtTemplate: Determines the texture of the Shirt. The content ID link pointing to the shirt template hosted on the Roblox website.

@roblox/globaltype/ShirtGraphic.documentation: Applies a texture to the front surface of a character's torso, used to display t-shirts.

@roblox/globaltype/ShirtGraphic.Color3: Determines the colorization to be applied to the ShirtGraphic texture.
@roblox/globaltype/ShirtGraphic.Graphic: The content ID link pointing to the ShirtGraphic texture hosted on the Roblox website. This property sets the texture associated with a t-shirt.
The direction of movement, tied to the keys A and D. Must be 1 (right), 0 (straight), or -1 (left). Will refresh back to 0 unless constantly set.
The direction of movement, tied to the keys W and S. Must be an integer 1 (forward), 0 (null), or -1 (reverse). Will refresh back to 0 unless constantly set.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardController..documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when any input state of the skateboard controller is updated.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.documentation: A SkateboardPlatform can be used to create a skateboard. When characters get on a skateboard, they are stuck to it until they press the escape key. Until then, the character uses skateboard animations and travels faster than a walking character.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.St: The direction of movement, tied to the keys A and D. Must be 1 (right), 0 (straight), or -1 (left). Will refresh back to 0 unless constantly set.
If true, wheels won't roll without user input.
@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.Th: The direction of movement, tied to the keys W and S. Must be an integer 1 (forward), 0 (null), or -1 (reverse). Will refresh back to 0 unless constantly set.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.Eq.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.Mo.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the SkateboardPlatform's SkateboardPlatform.ControllingHumanoid changes the force being used on the SkateboardPlatform.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.Un.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.eq.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/SkateboardPlatform.un.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Skin.documentation: Historically changed the colors of body parts to match the Skin.SkinColor property. Superceded by the BodyColors class.

@roblox/globaltype/Sky.CelestialBodiesSh: Sets whether the Sun, Moon, and stars will show.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.MoonAngularSize: The perceived angular size of the moon while using this skybox, in degrees.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.MoonTextureId: The texture of the moon while using this skybox.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SkyboxBk: The URL link to a picture for the back surface of the sky.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SkyboxDn: The URL asset link to a picture for the Bottom surface of the sky.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SkyboxFt: The URL link to a picture for the front surface of the skybox.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SkyboxLf: The URL link to a picture for the left surface of the sky.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SkyboxRt: The URL link to a picture for the right surface of the sky.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SkyboxUp: The URL link to a picture for the top surface of the sky.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.StarCount: How many stars are shown in the skybox.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SunAngularSize: The perceived angular size of the sun while using this skybox, in degrees.
@roblox/globaltype/Sky.SunTextureId: The texture of the sun while using this skybox.

@roblox/globaltype/SlidingBallConstraint.documentation: A currently unfinished and unavailable type of constraint.

@roblox/globaltype/SlidingBallConstraint: Sets whether the translation of the PrismaticConstraint is actuated and, if so, what kind of actuation.
Sets whether the SlidingBallConstraint will limit the range of translation.
Specifies the sharpness of the linear servo motor in reaching the SlidingBallConstraint.TargetPosition.
The lower position limit along the x-axis of Constraint.Attachment0 for a SlidingBallConstraint if SlidingBallConstraint.LimitsEnabled is true.
The maximum acceleration a SlidingBallConstraint with SlidingBallConstraint.ActuatorType set to Enum.ActuatorType can apply when trying to reach its desired SlidingBallConstraint.Velocity.
The maximum force a SlidingBallConstraint with SlidingBallConstraint.ActuatorType set to Enum.ActuatorType can apply when trying to reach its desired SlidingBallConstraint.Velocity.

How elastic Attachment connected by a SlidingBallConstraint will be when they reach the end of the range specified by SlidingBallConstraint.UpperLimit and SlidingBallConstraint.LowerLimit when SlidingBallConstraint.LimitsEnabled is set to true. Constrained between 0 and 1.
The maximum force a SlidingBallConstraint with SlidingBallConstraint.ActuatorType set to Enum.ActuatorType can apply when trying to reach its desired SlidingBallConstraint.Speed.

The desired speed a SlidingBallConstraint with SlidingBallConstraint.ActuatorType set to Enum.ActuatorType will attempt to maintain while translating towards its SlidingBallConstraint.TargetPosition. Measured in studs/second.
The target position a SlidingBallConstraint will attempt to translate to if its SlidingBallConstraint.ActuatorType is set to Enum.ActuatorType. Measured in studs.
The upper position limit along the x-axis of Constraint.Attachment0 for a SlidingBallConstraint if SlidingBallConstraint.LimitsEnabled is true.
The velocity a SlidingBallConstraint with SlidingBallConstraint.ActuatorType set to Enum.ActuatorType will attempt to achieve. Measured in studs/second.

@roblox/globaltype/Smoke.documentation: A particle emitter with the visual aesthetic of smoke

@roblox/globaltype/Smoke.Color: Determines the color of the smoke particles
@roblox/globaltype/Smoke.RiseVelocity: Determines the velocity of the smoke particles
@roblox/globaltype/Smoke.Size: Determines the size of newly emit smoke particles

@roblox/globaltype/Snap.documentation: Holds two parts together and functions identically to Weld

@roblox/globaltype/SocialService.documentation: Facilitates social functions that impact relationships made on the Roblox platform

@roblox/globaltype/SocialService.PromptG: The player to prompt with the game invite screen

@roblox/globaltype/SocialService.PromptG.documentation: Prompts the given Player with the game invite screen

@roblox/globaltype/SocialService.CanSend: The player instance of the user used to determine if the client can send a game invite
Whether the specified player can send a game invite

@roblox/globaltype/SocialService.CanSend.documentation: Indicates whether the given Player can invite other players

@roblox/globaltype/SocialService.GameInv.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a player closes a game invite prompt

@roblox/globaltype/SolidModelContentProv.documentation: An internal service which serves no functionality to developers.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.documentation: A Sound is an object that emits sound. Sounds can be placed within a BasePart or Attachment to emit a sound from a particular position within a place or world, or it can be attached elsewhere to play the sound at a constant volume throughout the entire place.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.IsLoaded: This property will be true when the Sound has loaded loaded from Roblox servers and is ready to play.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.IsPaused: This read-only property will return true when the Sound is not playing.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.IsPlaying: This read-only property will return true when the Sound is playing.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Looped: This sets whether or not the Sound repeats once it has finished when it is playing.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.PlayOnRemove: When true, the Sound will play when it is removed from the game, by parenting the Sound or one if its ancestors to nil.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.PlaybackLoudnes: A number between 0 and 1000 indicating how loud the Sound is currently playing back.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.PlaybackSpeed: Determines the speed at which a Sound will play, with higher values causing the sound to play faster and at a higher pitch.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.RollOffMaxDista: The maximum distance, in studs, a client's listener can be from the Sound|Sound\s origin and still hear it. Only applies to Sounds parented to a Part or Attachment (3D sounds)
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.RollOffMinDista: The minimum distance, in studs, at which a 3D Sound (direct child of a BasePart or Attachment) will begin to attenuate (decrease in volume)
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.RollOffMode: Controls how the volume of a 3D Sound (parented to a BasePart or Attachment) behaves as the distance between the listener and sound's parent changes.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.SoundGroup: The SoundGroup that is linked to this Sound. Volume and SoundEffects applied to this sound group will pass onto the sound. A sound can only be in one sound group at a time.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.SoundId: This property is the content ID of the sound file a Sound object is associated with. Once a sound has been uploaded to Roblox the content ID can be found in the uploaded sound’s URL.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.TimeLength: The length of the Sound in seconds. If the Sound is not loaded, this value will be 0.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.TimePosition: Shows the progress in seconds of the Sound. Can be changed to move the playback position of the Sound both before and during playback.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Volume: The volume of the Sound. Can be set between 0 and 10. Defaults to 0.5
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.EmitterSize: The minimum distance, in studs, at which a 3D Sound (direct child of a BasePart or Attachment) will begin to attenuate (decrease in volume)
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.MaxDistance: The maximum distance, in studs, a client's listener can be from the Sound|Sound\s origin and still hear it. Only applies to Sounds parented to a Part or Attachment (3D sounds)
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.MinDistance: The minimum distance at which a 3D Sound (direct child of a BasePart or Attachment) will begin to attenuate. Effectively, the emitter size.
@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Pitch: Deprecated. Sets how high pitched and fast a Sound is when it is played. The greater the integer, the higher and faster the Sound is.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Pause.documentation: Sets Sound.Playing to false. This pauses the playback of the Sound if the sound is playing. As Sound.TimePosition is not reset ,when the Sound is resumed it will continue from its previous position.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Play.documentation: Plays the Sound. Sets Sound.TimePosition to the last value set by a Script (or 0 if it has not been set), and then sets Sound.Playing to true.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Resume.documentation: Resumes the Sound. Sets Sound.Playing to true. Does not alter Sound.TimePosition and thus can be used to resume the playback of a sound stopped using Sound:Pause.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Stop.documentation: Stops the Sound. Sets Sound.Playing to false then sets Sound.TimePosition to 0.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.DidLoop.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.DidLoop.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.DidLoop.documentation: Event that fires whenever the Sound loops. Returns soundId and numOfTimesLooped, giving the contentID of the sound and the number of times looped respectively.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Ended.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Ended.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Ended.documentation: Fires when the Sound has completed playback and stopped.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Loaded.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Loaded.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Paused.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Paused.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Played.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Played.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Played.documentation: Fires whenever the Sound is played using the Sound:Play function.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Resumed.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Resumed.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Stopped.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Stopped.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Sound.Stopped.documentation: Fires when the Sound is stopped due to the Sound:Stop function.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundEffect.documentation: SoundEffect is the base class that all other sound effects derive from. A SoundEffect can be applied to either a Sound or SoundGroup by being parented to either.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundEffect.Priority: Determines the order the effect will be applied in relation to other effects.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundGroup.documentation: A SoundGroup is used to manage the volume and sound effects on multiple Sounds at once. Sounds in the SoundGroup will have their volume and effects adjusted by the SoundGroup.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundGroup.Volume: The volume multiplier applied to Sounds that are in the SoundGroup. This value ranges from 0 to 10.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.documentation: A service that determines various aspects of how Sounds play in the game.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.AmbientR: The ambient sound environment preset used by SoundService.
@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.Distance: The number of studs to be considered a meter by SoundService when calculating 3D Sound volume attenuation.
@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.DopplerS: This property determines the degree to with a 3D Sounds pitch varies due to the Doppler effect.
@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.RespectF: Sets whether Sound playback from a client will replicate to the server.
@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.RolloffS: Sets how fast 3D Sound volume attenuates, or 'rolls off'.
@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.GetListe: The current Enum.ListenerType and what the listener has been set to. Dependent on Enum.ListenerType the listener could be a BasePart, a DataType.CFrame or nil.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.GetListe.documentation: GetListener returns SoundServices current listener type and what is set as listener.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.PlayLoca.documentation: Plays a Sound locally, meaning the sound will only be heard by the client calling this function, regardless of where it's parented to.

@roblox/globaltype/SoundService.SetListe: Dependent on the Enum.ListenerType. BasePart for 'ObjectPosition' or 'ObjectCFrame', DataType.CFrame for 'CFrame', nil for 'Camera'.

@roblox/globaltype/Sparkles.documentation: A particle emitter with the visual aesthetic of sparkles

@roblox/globaltype/Sparkles.Color: Determines the color of the sparkle particles.
@roblox/globaltype/Sparkles.SparkleColor: Determines the color of the sparkle particles.

@roblox/globaltype/SpawnerService.documentation: An internal service that is responsible for the behavior or SpawnLocations. Its functionality is not accessible to developers.

@roblox/globaltype/SpawnLocation.documentation: SpawnLocation, or "spawns" determine where a Player respawns when they die. They can be configured to allow only certain players to use each spawn, using Team. They also control how ForceField are set up for newly-spawned players.

@roblox/globaltype/SpawnLocation.AllowTe: Allows a Player to join the team by touching the SpawnLocation. When set to true, if a Player character comes into contact with the SpawnLocation, the player's Player.TeamColor will be set to SpawnLocation.TeamColor.
@roblox/globaltype/SpawnLocation.Duratio: The length of time, in seconds, that a ForceField will be applied to a Player character spawning at this SpawnLocation. If Duration is zero, the ForceField is never created, and it will not trigger the Instance.DescendantAdded or Instance.ChildAdded events.
@roblox/globaltype/SpawnLocation.Enabled: Sets whether or not the SpawnLocation is enabled. When disabled players cannot spawn at the SpawnLocation and the AllowTeamChangeOnTouch functionality is disabled.
@roblox/globaltype/SpawnLocation.Neutral: Whether or not a SpawnLocation is affiliated with a specific team. This means that any Player, of any Team, can spawn on it if this property is set to true.
@roblox/globaltype/SpawnLocation.TeamCol: Sets what team the SpawnLocation is affiliated to. If SpawnLocation.Neutral property is false, only Players with the same Player.TeamColor as the spawn's TeamColor will be able to spawn there.

@roblox/globaltype/SpecialMesh.documentation: The SpecialMesh is an object that allows developers to provide a standard template or user uploaded mesh to a BasePart.

@roblox/globaltype/SpecialMesh.MeshType: Determines the type of mesh that will be applied to the BasePart the SpecialMesh is parented to.

@roblox/globaltype/SphereHandleAdornment.documentation: The SphereHandleAdornment is a sphere that can be adorned to a BasePart.

@roblox/globaltype/SpotLight.documentation: A light source that emits light directionally in the shape of a cone with a spherical base.

@roblox/globaltype/SpotLight.Angle: The angle of which the light is shone from the SpotLight.
@roblox/globaltype/SpotLight.Face: Sets the side of the parent that the SpotLight comes from.
@roblox/globaltype/SpotLight.Range: The size of the area that the SpotLight will illuminate.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.Coil: The number of coils visualized on the SpringConstraint. This can only be set between 0 and 8.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.Damp: Damping constant for the SpringConstraint. Multiplied to the velocity of the constraintâ€™s Attachment to reduce the spring force applied.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.Limi: Sets whether the SpringConstraint enforces a minimum and maximum length.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.MaxF: The maximum force the SpringConstraint can apply on its Attachment.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.MaxL: The maximum separation the SpringConstraint will allow if SpringConstraint.LimitsEnabled is true.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.MinL: The minimum separation the SpringConstraint will allow if SpringConstraint.LimitsEnabled is true.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.Radi: The visualized radius of the spring's coils.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.Stif: The strength of the spring. The higher this value the more force will be applied when the attachments are separated a different length than the SpringConstraint.FreeLength.
@roblox/globaltype/SpringConstraint.Thic: The visualized thickness of the spring's coils.

@roblox/globaltype/StarterGear.documentation: If the game allows gear, StarterGear contains all of a player's appropriate gear. Whenever the Player's character spawns, all of the contents of that player's StarterGear will get copied into the player's Backpack.

@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.documentation: A container for LayerCollector|GUI objects to be copied into the PlayerGui of Player. Also provides a range of functions for interacting with the CoreGui

@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.ProcessUse: Allows the StarterGui service to process input like PlayerGui and CoreGui do
@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.ScreenOrie: Sets the default Enum/ScreenOrientation|screen orientation mode for users with mobile devices
@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.ShowDevelo: Determines whether the contents of StarterGui is visible in studio
@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.ResetPlaye: Determines whether each child parented to the StarterGui will be cloned into a player's PlayerGui when that player's character is respawned.

@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.GetCoreGui.documentation: Returns whether the given Enum.CoreGuiTypeis enabled or if it has been disabled using StarterGui:SetCoreGuiEnabled

@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.SetCoreGui: Whether to enable or disable the given Enum.CoreGuiType

@roblox/globaltype/StarterGui.GetCore.documentation: Returns a variable that has been specified by a Roblox CoreScript

@roblox/globaltype/StarterPack.documentation: A service-level container whose contents are copied into each Player's Backpack when the player spawns. It is generally used to hold Tools, but is sometimes used to hold LocalScripts to ensure that each player gets a copy.

@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.documentation: A service which allows the defaults of properties in the Player object to be set.

@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.AllowCu: Describes the current game's permission levels regarding custom avatar animations from the website
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.AutoJum: Sets whether the character will automatically jump when hitting an obstacle on a mobile device.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.CameraM: The maximum distance the player's default camera is allowed to zoom out in studs.
The minimum distance in studs the player's default camera is allowed to zoom in.
Changes the default camera's mode to either first or third person.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.DevCame: Sets how the default camera handles objects between the camera and the player.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.DevComp: Lets developer overwrite the default camera mode for each player if the player is on a computer.
Lets developer overwrite the player's movement mode if the player is on a computer.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.DevTouc: Lets developer overwrite the default camera movement mode for each player if the player is on a mobile device.
Lets developer overwrite the player's movement mode if the player is on a touch device.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.EnableM: Determines if a player can toggle mouse lock by default.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.HealthD: Sets the distance at which this player will see other Humanoid’s health bars. If set to 0, the health bars will not be displayed.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.LoadCha: Whether or not the appearance of a player's character should be loaded.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.NameDis: Sets the distance at which this player will see other Humanoid’s names. If set to 0, names are hidden.
@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayer.UserEmo: Determines if user-owned emotes are loaded when loading avatars.

@roblox/globaltype/StarterPlayerScripts.documentation: A container for objects to be copied to a Player's PlayerScripts when they join a game

@roblox/globaltype/Stats.ContactsCount: A measurement of how many parts are currently in contact with one another.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.DataReceiveKbps: In a networked game, this describes roughly how many kilobytes of data are being received by the current instance, per second.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.DataSendKbps: In a networked game, this describes roughly how many kilobytes of data are being sent by the current instance, per second.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.HeartbeatTimeMs: A measurement of the total amount of time it takes long it takes for Roblox to update all of its Task Scheduler jobs, in milliseconds.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.InstanceCount: A measurement of how many Instance are currently in memory.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.MovingPrimitive: A measurement of how many physically simulated components are currently moving in the game world.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.PhysicsReceiveK: In a networked game, this describes roughly how many kilobytes of physics data are being received by the current instance, per second.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.PhysicsSendKbps: In a networked game, this describes roughly how many kilobytes of physics data are being sent by the current instance, per second.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.PhysicsStepTime:
A measurement of how long it takes for the physics engine to update its current state, in milliseconds.
If this value is high, then it means the game instance is under stress from the physics simulations taking place.
@roblox/globaltype/Stats.PrimitivesCount: A measurement of how many physically simulated components currently exist in the game world.

@roblox/globaltype/Stats.GetMemoryUsageM.documentation: Returns the number of megabytes that are being consumed in the specified DeveloperMemoryTag category.

@roblox/globaltype/Stats.GetTotalMemoryU.documentation: Returns the total amount of memory being consumed by the current game session, in megabytes.

@roblox/globaltype/StatsItem.GetValueStr.documentation: Returns the StatsItem's value as a formatted string.

@roblox/globaltype/Status.documentation: An unfinished object which offers no functionality to developers.

@roblox/globaltype/StringValue.documentation: A container object for a single string.

@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Always Save Sc: If set to true, Roblox Studio will attempt to transfer script changes that were made during a Play Solo session to the opened place.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Animate Hover: If set to true, the hover selection box that is shown when mousing over selectable objects in the Workspace will flash between Studio/Hover Over Color and Studio/Select Color based on the Studio/Hover Animate Speed.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Background Col: Specifies the background color of Roblox Studio's script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Basic Objects: Sets the scrolling mode of the Advanced Objects tab in Roblox Studio.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Built-in Funct: Sets the color of built-in functions and keywords in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Camera Mouse W: Sets how many studs the camera will move forward or backwards when using the mouse wheel.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Camera Shift S: Sets the speed in studs/sec that the camera moves while holding down Shift with the movement keys.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Camera Speed: Sets the speed in studs/sec that the camera moves when movement keys are pressed.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Clear Output O: If set to true, the output will be automatically cleared when game sessions are switched.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Comment Color: Specifies the color of comments in Roblox Studio's script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.DefaultScriptF: Specifies the default prompt directory that will be opened when the user activates the Execute Script button in Roblox Studio.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.DeprecatedObje: If set to true, deprecated objects will be shown in the Advanced Objects window, as well as the Object Browser.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Drag Multiple: If set to true, the bounding box of a selection will be used for collision detection while dragging, instead of each individual part being checked. This makes the dragger perform smoother, but with notably less precision.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Enable Autocom: When set to true, the script editor and command bar will show an autocomplete menu while writing.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Error Color: Specifies the color of the wavy underline shown when malformed code is detected in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Find Selection: Sets the highlight color of matches in the script editor's Find Selection operation (Ctrl+F).
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Font: Specifies the font used in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Hover Animate: Specifies how frequently the hover animation flashes when the mouse is hovering over a selectable object in the Workspace.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Hover Over Col: Specifies the color that the hover selection box uses.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Keyword Color: Sets the text color of built-in Lua keywords.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Line Thickness: Sets the thickness of the Model.PrimaryPart selection adornee. This value is constrained between 0 and 0.05
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.LuaDebuggerEna: Specifies whether or not the Lua Debugger feature is enabled.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Matching Word: Sets the highlight color of double-clicked variables in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Maximum Output: The maximum number of lines that can be displayed in the output.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Number Color: Specifies the color of numbers in Roblox Studio's script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Only Play Audi: If set to true, audio being played will only be heard if the game window is being focused on.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Operator Color: Sets the text color of operator characters in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Output Font: Specifies the font used by the output.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Output Layout: Sets the layout mode of the output.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.OverrideCoreSc: If set to true, the Studio.OverrideCoreScriptsDir will be used for CoreScripts in Roblox Studio, instead of the default rbxasset://scripts directory.
The directory used when overriding core scripts. This should point to a clone of Roblox's CoreScript GitHub repository.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.PermissionLeve: Sets the highest permission level that APIs have to have in order to be shown in the Object Browser. See Enum.PermissionLevelShown for more info.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.PluginsDir: The directory where local plugins are stored.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Render Throttl: Scales how much rendering will be throttled when the game window isn't being focused on. In practice, this property isn't very well understood, and is probably intended for internal use only.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Respect Studio: When set to true, Roblox Studio shortcuts will take priority over inputs being captured in the game window.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.ScriptTimeoutL: The time (in seconds) a script can wait to be resumed before timing out.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Select Color: The color of the selection box used with object selections in the Workspace
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Select: Sets the color of the Model.PrimaryPart selection box.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Selection Back: Sets the background color of selected text in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Selection Colo: Sets the text color of selected text in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Server Audio B: An unused Roblox Studio setting that does not appear to have any functionality.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Show Core GUI: If set to true, the CoreGui will be visible in the Explorer while the game is running.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Show Diagnosti: If set to true, basic diagnostic information is shown in the bottom right.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Show Hover Ove: If set to true, hovering over an object in the Workspace will show a selection box.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Show Navigatio: When set to true, the navigation mesh used by the PathfindingService will be visualized.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Show Plugin GU: When set to true, the PluginGuiService will be shown in Roblox Studio's explorer.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Show QT warnin: If set to true, certain internal error messages regarding the QT framework that Roblox uses will be shown in the output.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.String Color: Specifies the color of strings in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Tab Width: Specifies how many spaces are used to represent a tab in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Text Color: Specifies the color of normal text in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Text Wrapping: If set to true, text in the script editor will be wrapped.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Theme: Used to get/set current StudioTheme used by Studio
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.Warning Color: Specifies the color of the wavy underline shown when the script analyzer picks up a problem that should be addressed in the script editor.
@roblox/globaltype/Studio.UI Theme: Specifies the color scheme of Roblox Studio.

@roblox/globaltype/StudioService.GridSiz: Determines the distance in studs by which studio's drag and move tools move objects each tick
@roblox/globaltype/StudioService.RotateI: Determines the degrees by which studio's rotation tool will rotate selected objects each tick
@roblox/globaltype/StudioService.StudioL: The locale currently in-use by Studio, e.g. en_US.
@roblox/globaltype/StudioService.UseLoca: Determines whether studio tools will use local space of an object or global space.
