For example, {"jpg", "png"} would allow only a JPG or PNG file to be selected. If no filter is provided, the filter is nil and allows the user to select any file type
The imported File. Returns nil if no files were selected, or if the selected file was too large (FileSize greater than 100 megabytes)

@roblox/globaltype/StudioService.PromptI.documentation: Prompts the current Studio user to select one file to add as a File

For example, {"jpg", "png"} would allow only JPG and PNG files to be selected. If no filter is provided, the filter is nil and allows the user to select any file type.
The imported File. Returns an empty list if no files were selected. Returns nil if the user selected one or more files that were too large (FileSize greater than 100 megabytes)

@roblox/globaltype/StudioService.PromptI.documentation: Prompts the current Studio user to select files to add as File

The modifier you want to place on the StyleGuideColor element

@roblox/globaltype/SunRaysEffect.Intensi: Determines the opacity of the sun rays
@roblox/globaltype/SunRaysEffect.Spread: Determines how wide the sun rays will spread out

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceAppearance.documentation: An object that allows developers to override the appearance of a MeshPart with advanced graphics options

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceAppearance.Alp: Determines how the alpha channel of the SurfaceAppearance.ColorMap of a SurfaceAppearance is used
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceAppearance.Col: Determines the color and opacity of the surface
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceAppearance.Met: Determines which parts of the surface are metal and are non-metal

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceAppearance.Rou: Determines the apparent roughness across the surface

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.documentation: Container for GuiObjects that are rendered on the surface of a part

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.Active: Whether or not mouse events will be passed to objects layered below.

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.Brightness: Determines the factor by which the GUI's light is scaled when SurfaceGui.LightInfluence is 0.

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.ClipsDesce: When set to true, portions of GuiObjects that fall outside of the SurfaceGui's canvas borders will not be drawn.
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.Face: The face that the SurfaceGui is rendered on.
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.LightInflu: Controls how much the SurfaceGui is influenced by the lighting in the game world.
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.PixelsPerS: Determines the number of screen-space pixels per world-space stud used to render the contents of the SurfaceGui
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.ToolPunchT: Sets the distance left clicking starts acting on the surface gui instead of the held tool.
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceGui.ZOffset: Offsets the SurfaceGui relative to the normal of the surface it is attached to.

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceLight.documentation: A light source that emits illumination of a specified color and brightness from a face for a specified range.

@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceLight.Angle: The angle of which the light is shone from the SurfaceLight.
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceLight.Face: Sets the side of the parent that the SurfaceLight comes from.
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceLight.Range: The distance from the SurfaceLight's face that will illuminate.
@roblox/globaltype/SurfaceSelection.Targ: Sets which side the SurfaceSelection will appear on, on the adorned BasePart.

The current average rate of the task scheduler.
@roblox/globaltype/TaskScheduler.ThreadP: The specified thread pooling configuration for the task scheduler.
The current size of the thread pool.

@roblox/globaltype/Team.AutoAssignable: This property determines whether Players will be automatically placed onto the Team when joining. If multiple teams have this property set to true, Roblox will attempt to even the teams out when Players are added.
@roblox/globaltype/Team.TeamColor: This property sets the color of the Team. Determines the Player.TeamColor property of players who are a member of the team. Also determines the color displayed on the player list and above player's heads.
@roblox/globaltype/Team.AutoColorCharact: Deprecated and no longer functional. Historically set whether or not Player character models on a team would be colored to Team.TeamColor.
@roblox/globaltype/Team.Score: Deprecated. This property can be used to store an integer value associated with the team. This property offers no additional functionality and is not used by any game services.

@roblox/globaltype/Team.GetPlayers.documentation: Returns a list of Players who are assigned to the Team. A Player is considered assigned if their Player.Team property is equal to the Team and Player.Neutral is false.

@roblox/globaltype/Team.PlayerAdded.documentation: Fires whenever a Player is assigned to the Team. A player is considered assigned if their Player.Team property is equal to the Team and Player.Neutral is false.

@roblox/globaltype/Team.PlayerRemoved.documentation: Fires whenever a Player is removed from a Team. This can be due to the Player leaving the game, Player.Neutral being set to true or the Player joining a different team.

@roblox/globaltype/Teams.documentation: The Teams service holds a game's Team objects. Team objects must be parented to the Teams service.

@roblox/globaltype/Teams.GetTeams.documentation: Returns a table containing the game's Team objects. Will only return Team objects that are parented to the Teams service.

@roblox/globaltype/Teams.RebalanceTeams.documentation: Evens the number of people on each team. This function does not work correctly and should not be used.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.MaterialColor:
MaterialColors represents the editor for the Material Color feature, and cannot be edited by scripts.

To get the color of a material, use: Terrain:GetMaterialColor To set the color of a material, use: Terrain:SetMaterialColor

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.WaterReflecta: Controls how opaque the Terrain's water reflections are.
@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.WaterWaveSize: Sets the maximum height of the Terrain water waves in studs.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.FillBlock/par: The cframe (position and orientation) of the terrain block
The size in studs of the square block - both the height and width

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.FillBlock.documentation: Fills a block of smooth terrain with a given location, rotation, size, and material

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.FillCylinder/: The cframe (position and orientation) of the terrain block
The height in studs of the terrain ball
The radius in studs of the terrain cylinder

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.FillCylinder.documentation: Fills a cylinder of smooth terrain in a given space.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.FillRegion.documentation: Fills a Region3 space with smooth terrain.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.FillWedge/par: The position and orientation of the wedge to fill
The size of the wedge to fill
The material with which the wedge will be filled

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.FillWedge.documentation: Fills a wedge-shaped volume of Terrain with the given enum.Material and the area's CFrame and Size.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.GetMaterialCo.documentation: Returns current terrain material color for specified terrain material.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.PasteRegion.documentation: Applies a chunk of terrain to the Terrain object. Note: TerrainRegion data does not replicate between server and client.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.ReadVoxels/pa: Target region to write to. Must be aligned to the voxel grid. Will throw an error if region is too large.
@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.ReadVoxels/re: Returns raw voxel data as two 3D arrays. - materials - 3D array of Enum.Material from the target area. Also contains a Size field, equal to the dimensions of the nested arrays. - occupancies - 3D array of occupancy values from the target area. Also contains a Size field, equal to the dimensions of the nested arrays.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.ReadVoxels.documentation: Returns a certain region of smooth terrain in table format

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.ReplaceMateri: The region in which the replacement operation will occur
The resolution at which the replacement operation will take place; at the moment this must be exactly 4.
The old material that shall be replaced

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.ReplaceMateri.documentation: Replaces the terrain of a material within a region with another material

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.SetMaterialCo.documentation: Sets current terrain material color for specified terrain material.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.WorldToCell.documentation: Returns the grid cell location that contains the point position.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.WorldToCellPr.documentation: Returns the grid cell location that contains the point position, preferring empty grid cells when position is on a grid edge.
Returns the grid cell location that contains the point position, preferring non-empty grid cells when position is on a grid edge.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.WriteVoxels/p: Target region to write to. Must be aligned to the voxel grid. Will throw an error if region is too large.
3D array of Enum.Material. Dimensions must exactly match the size of the target region in voxels.
3D array of voxel occupancies (number between 0 and 1). Dimensions must exactly match the size of the target region in voxels.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.WriteVoxels.documentation: Sets a certain region of smooth terrain using the table format

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.ConvertToSmoo.documentation: Transforms the legacy terrain engine into the new terrain engine.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.GetCell.documentation: Returns the closest CellMaterial from the legacy terrain engine that matches the smooth terrain voxel specified.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.GetWaterCell.documentation: Returns if the cell is a water cell.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.SetCell.documentation: Sets the occupancy and material of a specific terrain voxel.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.SetCells.documentation: Sets the occupancy and material of all terrain voxels in a specific region.

@roblox/globaltype/Terrain.SetWaterCell.documentation: Sets the specified terrain voxel's material to ''Water'' and sets its occupancy to 1.

@roblox/globaltype/TerrainRegion.SizeInC: The size of this TerrainRegion in cells.
@roblox/globaltype/TerrainRegion.IsSmoot: The state of this property shows whether or not this TerrainRegion contains smooth terrain.

@roblox/globaltype/TerrainRegion.Convert.documentation: Transforms the TerrainRegion so it can be used with smooth terrain.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.documentation: A service used by Roblox to run controlled tests of the engine. It is available for developers to use, to a limited degree.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.AutoRuns: If set to true, the game will start running when the TestService's TestService:Run method is called.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Descripti: A description of the test being executed.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.ErrorCoun: Measures how many errors have been recorded in the test session.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.ExecuteWi: When set to true, the TestService will be executed when using the Run action in Roblox Studio.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Is30FpsTh: Sets whether or not the physics engine should be throttled to 30 FPS while the test is being ran.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.IsPhysics: Sets whether or not the physics environment should be throttled while running this test.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.IsSleepAl: Sets whether or not physics objects will be allowed to fall asleep while the test simulation is running.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.NumberOfP: The number of players expected in this test, if any.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.SimulateS: Sets a specific amount of additional latency experienced by players during the test session.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.TestCount: Measures how many test calls have been recorded in the test session.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Timeout: The maximum amount of time that tests are allowed to run for.
@roblox/globaltype/TestService.WarnCount: Measures how many warning calls have been recorded in the test session.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Checkpoin.documentation: Prints "Test checkpoint: ", followed by text, to the output, in blue text.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Done.documentation: Prints Testing Done to the output, in blue text.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Error.documentation: Prints a red message to the output.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Fail.documentation:
Indicates a fatal error in a TestService run.

If this is called inside of a script running inside of the TestService, this will initiate a breakpoint on the line that invoked the error.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Message.documentation: Prints Test message, followed by text to the output, in blue text.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Require.documentation: Prints whether a condition is true along with description text.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Warn.documentation: Prints if a condition is true, otherwise prints a warning.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.Run.documentation: Runs scripts which are parented to TestService.

@roblox/globaltype/TestService.ServerCol.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the server should collect a conditional test result.
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the server should collect a test result.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.documentation: A 2D user interface element that displays player-editable text

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.ClearTextOnFo: Determines whether clicking on the TextBox will clear its TextBox.Text property
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.CursorPositio: Determines the offset of the text cursor in bytes, or -1 if there is no cursor.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.Font: Determines the font used to render text
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.LineHeight: Scales the spacing between lines of text in the TextBox
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.MultiLine: When set to true, text inside a TextBox is able to move onto multiple lines. This also enables players to use the enter key to move onto a new line.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.PlaceholderCo: Sets the text color that gets used when no text has been entered into the TextBox yet.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.PlaceholderTe: Sets the text that gets displayed when no text has been entered into the TextBox yet.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.RichText: Determines whether the TextBox renders the TextBox.Text string using rich text formatting.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.SelectionStar: Determines the starting position of a text selection, or -1 if no text is selected
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.ShowNativeInp: If set to true, input native to the platform is used instead of Roblox's built-in keyboard.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.Text: Determines the string rendered by the UI element.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextBounds: The pixel size of a UI element's text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextEditable: Determines whether the user can change the TextBox.Text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextFits: Whether the text fits within the constraints of the TextBox.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextScaled: Changes whether text is resized to fit the GUI object that renders it.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextSize: Determine the line height of text in pixels.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextStrokeCol: Determines the color of the text stroke (outline).
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextStrokeTra: Determines the transparency of the text stroke (outline).
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextTruncate: Controls the truncation of the text displayed in this TextBox.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextWrapped: Determines if text wraps to multiple lines within the GuiObject element space, truncating excess text
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextXAlignmen: Determines the horizontal alignment of rendered text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.TextYAlignmen: Determines the vertical alignment of rendered text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.FontSize: Determines the font size of a TextBox object

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.CaptureFocus.documentation: Forces the client to focus on the TextBox.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.IsFocused.documentation: Returns true if the textbox is focused, or false if it is not.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.ReleaseFocus.documentation: Forces the client to unfocus the TextBox.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.FocusLost.Con.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.FocusLost.Wai.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.FocusLost.documentation: The FocusLost event fires when the client lets their focus off the TextBox.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.Focused.Conne.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.Focused.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/TextBox.ReturnPressed.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.documentation: A 2D user interface element that displays interactive text

@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.Font: Determines the font used to render text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.LineHeight: Scales the spacing between lines of text in the TextButton
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.LocalizedT: Sets whether a TextButton should be GuiBase2d.Localize or not.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.RichText: Determines whether the TextButton renders the TextButton.Text string using rich text formatting.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.Text: Determines the string rendered by the UI element.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextBounds: The pixel size of a UI element's text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextFits: A boolean representation of whether the TextButton's text fits within the size of it.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextScaled: Changes whether text is resized to fit within the TextButton.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextSize: Determine the line height of text in pixels.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextStroke: Determines the color of the text stroke (outline).
Determines the transparency of the text stroke (outline).
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextTrunca: Controls the truncation of the text displayed in this TextButton.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextWrappe: Determines if text wraps to multiple lines within the TextButton element space, truncating excess text
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextXAlign: Determines the horizontal alignment of rendered text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextYAlign: Determines the vertical alignment of rendered text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.FontSize: Determines the font size to be used
@roblox/globaltype/TextButton.TextWrap: Determines whether or not text should wrap at the edges of the object

@roblox/globaltype/TextFilterResult.GetC.documentation: Returns the text in a properly filtered manner for the specified Player.UserId.

@roblox/globaltype/TextFilterResult.GetN.documentation: Returns the text in a properly filtered manner for all users.
Returns the text in a properly filtered manner for the specified Player.UserId. This should be used in the context of non-chat text that another user can see, such as the name of a pet.

@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.documentation: A 2D user interface element that displays non-interactive text

@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.Font: Determines the font used to render text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.LineHeight: Scales the spacing between lines of text in the TextLabel
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.LocalizedTe: Sets whether a TextLabel should be GuiBase2d.Localize or not.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.RichText: Determines whether the TextLabel renders the TextLabel.Text string using rich text formatting.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.Text: Determines the string rendered by the UI element.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextBounds: The pixel size of a UI element's text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextColor3: This property determines the color of rendered text
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextFits: Enables when rendered text content does not fit within the UI element's space.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextScaled: Determines whether text in a UI element is scaled to fill the UI element
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextSize: Determine the line height of text in pixels.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextStrokeC: Determines the color of the text stroke (outline).
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextStrokeT: Determines the transparency of the text stroke (outline).
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextTruncat: Controls the truncation of the text displayed in this TextLabel.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextWrapped: Determines if text wraps to multiple lines within the TextLabel element space, truncating excess text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextXAlignm: Determines the horizontal alignment of rendered text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextYAlignm: Determines the vertical alignment of rendered text.
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.FontSize: Determines the height in pixels of one line of text
@roblox/globaltype/TextLabel.TextWrap: Determines if text wraps to multiple lines within the UI element space, truncating excess text

@roblox/globaltype/TextService.documentation: The TextService is a service internally responsible for handling the display of text in the game.

@roblox/globaltype/TextService.GetTextSi: The string for which the text size is to be calculated.
The integer representing the font size used.
The TextLabel.AbsoluteSize of the text object to be used. Required to compute how the text will wrap.
The size of the space required, in pixels, by the string with the specified formatting.

@roblox/globaltype/TextService.GetTextSi.documentation: Computes the DataType.Vector2 dimensions (in pixels) that will be taken up with text when using the specified formatting parameters and size constraints.

@roblox/globaltype/TextService.FilterStr: The userId of the player filtering the text.
The context that the filtered message will be used in. The default is PrivateChat.
Can be used to distribute the correctly filtered text accordingly.

@roblox/globaltype/TextService.FilterStr.documentation: Filters a string being received from a user, and returns a TextFilterResult which can be used to distribute the correctly filtered text accordingly.

@roblox/globaltype/Texture.documentation: A Texture object applies a repeating texture to the face of a BasePart.

@roblox/globaltype/Texture.OffsetStudsU: Determines the offset in studs of the rendered texture's horizontal coordinate.
@roblox/globaltype/Texture.OffsetStudsV: Determines the offset in studs of the rendered texture's vertical coordinate.
@roblox/globaltype/Texture.StudsPerTileU: Sets the horizontal size, in studs, of the tiled image applied by the Texture.
@roblox/globaltype/Texture.StudsPerTileV: Sets the vertical size, in studs, of the tiled image applied by the Texture.

@roblox/globaltype/ThirdPartyUserService.documentation: An internal service that is used to handle third-party related users.

@roblox/globaltype/TimerService.documentation: An internal service responsible for scheduling timed events. It is used by the Debris class. Its functionality can not be accessed by developers.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.documentation: An object, such as a weapon, that can be equipped by a Humanoid

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.CanBeDropped: Controls whether the player can drop the tool
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Enabled: Relates to whether or not the tool can be used
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Grip: Stores the Tool's Grip properties as one CFrame
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.GripForward: One of the properties that specifies a Tool's orientation in a character's hand. This represents the R02, R12, and R22 values of the Grip CFrame's rotation matrix
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.GripPos: The positional offset of a Tool weld matrix
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.GripRight: One of the properties that specifies a Tool's orientation in a character's hand. This represents the R00, R10, and R20 values of the Grip CFrame's rotation matrix
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.GripUp: One of the properties that specifies a Tool's orientation in a character's hand. This represents the R01, R11, and R21 values of the Grip CFrame's rotation matrix
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.ManualActivation: The ManualActivationOnly property controls whether the Tool can be activated without executing Tool:Activate
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.RequiresHandle: Determines whether a tool functions without a handle
@roblox/globaltype/Tool.ToolTip: Controls the message displayed when the player's mouse hovers over the tool in their backpack

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Activated.Connec.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Activated.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Activated.documentation: Fired when the player clicks while a tool is equipped

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Deactivated.Conn.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Deactivated.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Deactivated.documentation: Fired when the left mouse button is released.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Equipped.Connect.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Equipped.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Unequipped.Conne.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/Tool.Unequipped.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Torque.documentation: A constraint used to apply a torque to a part or assembly

@roblox/globaltype/Torque.RelativeTo: The CFrame in which the Torque is expressed.
@roblox/globaltype/Torque.Torque: The strength and direction of the torque.

@roblox/globaltype/TorsionSpringConstrai.documentation: A rotational spring that opposes the angular motion between two axes

@roblox/globaltype/TorsionSpringConstrai: The number of coils visualized for the constraint
Indicates the current angle, in degrees, of the limiting cone
The max angle, in degrees, of the constraint’s limiting cone
Maximum allowable torque provided by the spring
The restitution coefficient of the cone constraint
Determines whether the angular motion of attachments’ secondary axes is limited

@roblox/globaltype/TouchInputService.documentation: An internal service responsible for touch inputs on mobile devices.

@roblox/globaltype/TouchTransmitter.documentation: An internal object used by networking and replication code to transmit BasePart.Touched and BasePart.TouchEnded events.

@roblox/globaltype/Trail.documentation: The Trail object is used to create a trail like effect between two points.

@roblox/globaltype/Trail.Attachment0: Determines where the Trail will start drawing its segments.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.Attachment1: Determines where the Trail will start drawing its segments.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.Color: The color of the trail segments throughout the lifetime of the trail.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.Enabled: Toggles whether a trail will be drawn or not.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.FaceCamera: If set to true, the trail textures will always face the camera.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.LightEmission: Sets how much the colors of the trail are blended with the colors behind them.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.LightInfluence: Determines the factor to which the Trail is influenced by the environment's lighting
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.MaxLength: Sets the maximum length of the trail.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.MinLength: Minimum length of a trail's segment in studs.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.Texture: The texture to display on the trail.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.TextureLength: Sets length of texture if Trail.TextureMode is Wrap or Static. If mode is Stretch sets number of times texture will repeat.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.TextureMode: Sets how the Texture will be drawn.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.Transparency: Sets the transparency of the Trail's segments over the trail's Trail.Lifetime.
@roblox/globaltype/Trail.WidthScale: A DataType.NumberSequence that scales the width of the Trail over the course of its lifetime.

@roblox/globaltype/Translator.documentation: The role of a Translator is to manufacture/return strings localized for the viewing player

@roblox/globaltype/Translator.FormatByKe: The Key value to look up and translate.

If the Source text and translations contain articles/localization format strings|format strings, a Lua table of values or key-value pairs, depending on whether the format strings are numbered or named.

@roblox/globaltype/Translator.FormatByKe.documentation: Returns the localized text string in a LocalizationTable based on its Translator locale, by key.

@roblox/globaltype/Translator.Translate/: A valid in-game Instance to use for context override as outlined above. Note that this argument can be arbitrary, for example game, if you don't require a context override.
The Source text to look up and translate.

@roblox/globaltype/Translator.Translate.documentation: Returns the localized text string in a LocalizationTable based on its Translator locale, by source lookup.

@roblox/globaltype/TremoloSoundEffect.documentation: Creates a trembling effect on a sound by varying the volume of the sound up and down.

@roblox/globaltype/TremoloSoundEffect.De: Controls how much the volume will raise and lower.
@roblox/globaltype/TremoloSoundEffect.Du: Controls how long during one volume oscillation the effect will be active.
@roblox/globaltype/TremoloSoundEffect.Fr: Sets how often the effect will oscillate the volume.

@roblox/globaltype/TriangleMeshPart.documentation: Abstract intermediate class that manages physical geometry properties for PartOperations and MeshParts.

@roblox/globaltype/TriangleMeshPart.Coll: Determines the level of detail the part's physics will adhere to its mesh

@roblox/globaltype/TrussPart.documentation: Truss parts are the same as Part, except that they have a different visual style, resize differently and characters are able to climb them

@roblox/globaltype/TrussPart.Style: Sets what the truss looks like. There are currently three different styles.

@roblox/globaltype/Tween.documentation: Tweens are used to interpolate the properties of instances. The Tween object itself controls the playback of the interpolation. Creating and configuring tweens is done with the TweenService:Create function. This is the only way to create tweens. Instance.new cannot be used for this particular object.

@roblox/globaltype/Tween.Instance: The read-only Instance property of a Tween points to the Instance whose properties are being interpolated by the tween.
@roblox/globaltype/Tween.TweenInfo: Read-only property that includes information on how the interpolation of the Tween is to be carried out, using the TweenInfo data type.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.documentation: Abstract base class for in-between interpolation handlers. Tween inherits from BaseTween.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.PlaybackSta: PlaybackState describes the current stage for the Tween animation. A description of each state can be found on the page for the Enum.PlaybackState enum. It can be manipulated through other Tween functions, like Tween.Play.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.Cancel.documentation: The Cancel function halts playback of its Tween and resets the tween variables. If TweenBase:Play is called again the Tween's properties will resume interpolating towards their destination but, as the tween variables have been reset, take the full length of the animation to do so.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.Pause.documentation: The Pause function halts playback of its Tween. If TweenBase.Resume is called again the tween will resume playback from the moment it was paused.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.Play.documentation: The Play function starts the playback of its Tween. Note that if a tween has already begun calling Play will have no effect unless the tween has finished or has been stopped (either by TweenBase:Cancel or TweenBase:Pause).

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.Completed.C.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.Completed.W.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenBase.Completed.documentation: The Completed event of a Tween fires when the tween finishes playing. This will happen either when the tween naturally finishes playing, or if it is stopped with TweenBase:Cancel.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenService.documentation: TweenService is used to create Tweens, which are used to interpolate, or tween, the properties of instances. Tweens can be used on any object with compatible property types.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenService.Create/p: The Instance whose properties are to be tweened.
A dictionary of properties, and their target values, to be tweened.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenService.Create.documentation: Creates a new Tween given the object whose properties are to be tweened, a datatype.TweenInfo and a dictionary of goal property values.

@roblox/globaltype/TweenService.GetValue: A new alpha value generated from the given easing style and direction

@roblox/globaltype/TweenService.GetValue.documentation: Calculates a new alpha given an Enum.EasingStyle and Enum.EasingDirection

@roblox/globaltype/UIAspectRatioConstrai.documentation: Ensures the parent UI element maintains a particular aspect ratio.

@roblox/globaltype/UIAspectRatioConstrai: Determines the width-to-height ratio to be maintained by the constraint.
Determines what limits the maximum size of the UI element.
Determines the axis to use when setting the new size of the UI element.

@roblox/globaltype/UIBase.documentation: UIBase is the base class for UI layout and constraint classes.

@roblox/globaltype/UIComponent.documentation: A base class for UI constraint and layout classes, inherits from UiBase.

@roblox/globaltype/UIConstraint.documentation: The base class for UI constraint classes.

@roblox/globaltype/UICorner.documentation: A UIComponent that will apply deformation to shapes of corners of its parent GuiObject

@roblox/globaltype/UICorner.CornerRadius: Determines the radius, in pixels, of the UICorner UIComponent

@roblox/globaltype/UIGradient.documentation: A UIComponent, that blends a color gradient to its parent GuiObject, so you can layer multiple colors into your text, UI background or other UI content.

@roblox/globaltype/UIGradient.Color: Determines the color blended with the parent GuiObject along the length of the gradient
@roblox/globaltype/UIGradient.Enabled: Whether the gradient is enabled or not.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGradient.Offset: Determines the scalar translation of the gradient from the center of the parent GuiObject.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGradient.Rotation: Determines the clockwise rotation in degrees of the gradient starting from left to right.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGradient.Transparen: Determines how much the parent GuiObject can be seen through along the length of the gradient

@roblox/globaltype/UIGridLayout.documentation: Positions sibling UI elements by filling rows using the space of the parent UI element

@roblox/globaltype/UIGridLayout.CellPadd: Determines how much space there is between elements in the grid.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGridLayout.CellSize: Determines the size of each element in the grid.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGridLayout.FillDire: Determines the maximum number of cells that may be used in a row or column before before the next one is started.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGridLayout.StartCor: Determines from which corner the grid starts laying out UI elements.

@roblox/globaltype/UIGridStyleLayout.documentation: The base class for grid style UI layouts.

@roblox/globaltype/UIGridStyleLayout.Abs: The absolute size of space being taken up by the grid layout.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGridStyleLayout.Fil: Determines the axis in which UI elements are laid out.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGridStyleLayout.Hor: Determines the horizontal alignment of UI elements within the parent element.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGridStyleLayout.Sor: Determines the manner in which the next UI element is chosen when being laid out.
@roblox/globaltype/UIGridStyleLayout.Ver: Determines the vertical alignment of UI elements within the parent element.

@roblox/globaltype/UIGridStyleLayout.Set.documentation: Sets the function used to determine the order of elements when SortOrder is set to Custom.

@roblox/globaltype/UIInlineLayout.documentation: Aligns and renders text-based UI elements inline for the purposes of rich text formatting.

@roblox/globaltype/UILayout.documentation: The base class for UI layout classes.

@roblox/globaltype/UIListLayout.documentation: Positions sibling UI elements in a single row.

@roblox/globaltype/UIListLayout.Padding: Determines the amount of free space between each element.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPadding.PaddingBott: The padding to apply on the bottom side relative to the parent's normal size.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPadding.PaddingLeft: The padding to apply on the left side relative to the parent's normal size.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPadding.PaddingRigh: The padding to apply on the right side relative to the parent's normal size.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPadding.PaddingTop: The padding to apply on the top side relative to the parent's normal size.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.Animated: Whether or not to animate transitions between pages.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.Circular: Whether or not the page layout wraps around at the ends.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.CurrentP: The page that is either currently being displayed or is the target of the current animation.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.EasingDi: The easing direction to use when performing an animation.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.EasingSt: The easing style to use when performing an animation.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.GamepadI: Controls the overrides of NextSelection{Up, Down, Left, Right}. Defaults to true.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.Padding: Determines the amount that pages are separated from each other by.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.ScrollWh: Controls the use of scroll wheel, in case that it is intended for something else. Defaults to true.
@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.TouchInp: Controls touch scrolling, in case this is a non-interactive layout. Defaults to true.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.JumpTo.documentation: If the page is in the UIPageLayout, then it sets UIPageLayout.CurrentPage to it and animates to it. If the circular layout is enabled, it will take the shortest path to this page.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.JumpToIn.documentation: If the index is >= 0 and less than the size of the layout, this method acts like UIPageLayout:JumpTo. If it's out of bounds and circular is set, it will animate the full distance between the in-bounds index of UIPageLayout.CurrentPage and the new index.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.Next.documentation: Sets UIPageLayout.CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.Previous.documentation: Sets UIPageLayout.CurrentPage to the page before the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a previous page.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.PageEnte.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a page comes into view, and is going to be rendered.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.PageLeav.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a page leaves view, and will not be rendered.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.Stopped..documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/UIPageLayout.Stopped.documentation: Fires when an animation to UIPageLayout.CurrentPage is completed without being canceled, and the view stops scrolling.

@roblox/globaltype/UIScale.documentation: An object that acts as a multiplier for the size of the parent UI element's scale.

@roblox/globaltype/UIScale.Scale: Determines the multiplier to apply to the parent UI element's size.

@roblox/globaltype/UISizeConstraint.documentation: Ensures a GuiObject does not become larger or smaller than the constraint's max size or min size.

@roblox/globaltype/UISizeConstraint.MaxS: The largest size in pixels the object is allowed to be.
@roblox/globaltype/UISizeConstraint.MinS: The smallest size in pixels the object is allowed to be.

@roblox/globaltype/UIStroke.documentation: Applies an outline to text or a UI border

@roblox/globaltype/UIStroke.ApplyStrokeM: Determines whether to apply the stroke to the object’s border instead of the text itself
@roblox/globaltype/UIStroke.Transparency: Sets the stroke opacity independently of the parent object’s GuiObject.BackgroundTransparency or TextLabel.TextTransparency

@roblox/globaltype/UITableLayout.documentation: Lays out sibling UI elements and their child UI elements as rows/columns and cells in a table.

@roblox/globaltype/UITableLayout.FillEmp: Determines whether cells are sized such that they occupy the horizontal space of the parent UI element.
Determines whether cells are sized such that they occupy the vertical space of the parent UI element.
@roblox/globaltype/UITableLayout.MajorAx: Determines whether sibling UI elements are treated as rows or columns.

@roblox/globaltype/UITextSizeConstraint.documentation: Ensures that the size of text rendered by certain GuiObject classes lies within the range described by UITextSizeConstraint.MaxTextSize and UITextSizeConstraint.MinTextSize

The largest size in pixels the font is allowed to be
The smallest size in pixels the font is allowed to be

@roblox/globaltype/UnionOperation.documentation: Combines parts together into a single solid model

@roblox/globaltype/UniversalConstraint.documentation: A constraint that maintains a perpendicular angle between two axes of two attachments

@roblox/globaltype/UniversalConstraint.L: Determines whether the angular motion of attachments’ primary axes is limited
@roblox/globaltype/UniversalConstraint.M: The max angle, in degrees, of the constraint’s limiting cone
@roblox/globaltype/UniversalConstraint.R: The restitution coefficient of the cone constraint

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.documentation: The UserGameSettings is a singleton class found inside of the UserSettings singleton. It holds various persistent settings relating to how the user wants to control their camera, and their character.

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Comp: The camera movement mode currently in-use by the client.
The movement type in-use by the client via Computer input.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Cont: Toggles whether or not the client can use the Mouse Lock Switch mode.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Game: Describes how sensitive the camera is when using a gamepad.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Mast: A float between 0 and 1 representing the volume of the game's client.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Mous: A float representing the sensitivity of the client's mouse.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Rota: Controls how the client's character is rotated.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Save: The graphics quality level set by the client.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Touc: The camera type in-use by the client while on a mobile device.
The type of controls being used by the client on a mobile device.
@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.GetO: Whether or not the onboarding in particular has been completed yet

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.InFu.documentation: Returns true if the user's Roblox window is in full screen mode.

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.InSt.documentation: Returns true if the client's game session is in Roblox Studio.

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.SetC.documentation: If called, Roblox toggles the menu option to invert the user's camera y axis.

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.SetG.documentation: If called, Roblox toggles the menu option to control the camera sensitivity with gamepads.

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.SetO: The onboarding ID to set as completed

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Full.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires if the user's full screen mode is changed.

@roblox/globaltype/UserGameSettings.Stud.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

Fired when the user's client switches between studio mode and in-game mode.

This gets fired periodically in Roblox Studio when a session starts.

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.documentation: The UserInputService is a service used to detect the type of input available on a user's device via the use of a LocalScript. The service is also used to detect input events

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Acce: Describes whether the user's device has an accelerometer
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Game: Describes whether the device being used by a user has an available gamepad
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Gyro: Describes whether the user's device has a gyroscope
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Keyb: Describes whether the user’s device has a keyboard available
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Mous: Determines whether the user’s mouse can be moved freely or is locked
Scales the delta (change) output of the user's Mouse
Describes whether the user’s device has a mouse available
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.OnSc: Determines the position of the on-screen keyboard
Determines the size of the on-screen keyboard
Describes whether an on-screen keyboard is currently visible on the user's screen
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Touc: Describes whether the user’s current device has a touch-screen available
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.VREn: Indicates whether the user is using a virtual reality headset
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Moda: Toggles whether Roblox's mobile controls are hidden on mobile devices
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.User: Describes the orientation and position of a user's head, if they are actively using a virtual reality headset
@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Game: Whether the given gamepad supports a button corresponding with the given Enum.KeyCode

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Game.documentation: Returns whether the given Enum.UserInputType gamepad supports a button corresponding with the given Enum.KeyCode

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetC: An array of Enum.UserInputType corresponding with the gamepads connected to the user’s device

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetC.documentation: Returns an array of Enum.UserInputType gamepads currently connected

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetD.documentation: Returns an InputObject that describes the device's current acceleration
Returns an InputObject describing the device's current gravity vector

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetD:
A tuple containing two properties:

  1. The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened
  2. The CFrame is the device's current rotation relative to its default reference frame

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetD.documentation: Returns an InputObject and a DataType.CFrame,describing the device's current rotation vector

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetF.documentation: Returns the currently TextBox the client is currently focused on

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetG: Whether a gamepad associated with Enum.UserInputType is connected

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetG.documentation: Returns whether a gamepad with the given Enum.UserInputType''gamepadNum'' is connected

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetG: The Enum.UserInputType corresponding with the gamepad in question
An array of InputObject representing the current state of all available inputs for the given gamepad

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetG.documentation: Returns an array of InputObject for all available inputs on the given gamepad, representing each input’s last input state

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetK: An array of InputObject associated with the keys currently being pressed

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetK.documentation: Returns an array of InputObject associated with the Enum.KeyCode currently being pressed down

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetL: The Enum.UserInputType associated with the user’s most recent input

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetL.documentation: Returns the Enum.UserInputType associated with the user’s most recent input

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetM: An array of InputObject corresponding to the mouse buttons currently being currently held down

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetM.documentation: Returns an array of InputObject corresponding with the mouse buttons currently being held down
Returns the change, in pixels, of the position of the player’s Mouse in the last rendered frame. Only works if the mouse is locked

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetM: A DataType.Vector2 representing the current screen location of the mouse, in pixels

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetM.documentation: Returns the current screen location of the player's Mouse relative to the top left corner of the screen

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetN: An array of UserInputType that can be used for GUI navigation, in descending order of priority

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetN.documentation: Returns an array of Enum.UserInputType connected and enabled for GUI navigation in descending order of priority

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetS.documentation: Returns a string representing a key the user should press in order to input a given KeyCode

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetS: An array of Enum.KeyCode supported by the given gamepad

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetS.documentation: Returns an array of Enum.KeyCode that the gamepad associated with the given Enum.UserInputType supports

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetU: A DataType.CFrame describing the position and orientation of the specified VR device

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.GetU.documentation: Returns a DataType.CFrame describing the position and orientation of a specified virtual reality device

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsGa: Whether the specified gamepad button on the given gamepad is pressed is pressed

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsGa.documentation: Determines whether a particular button is pressed on a particular gamepad

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsKe: Whether the specified key is being held down

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsKe.documentation: Returns whether the given Enum.KeyCode is currently held down

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsMo: Whether the given mouse button is currently held down

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsMo.documentation: Returns whether the given Enum/UserInputType|mouse button is currently held down

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsNa: Whether the specified gamepad is a navigation gamepad

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.IsNa.documentation: Returns true if the specified Enum.UserInputTypeGamepad is allowed to control the navigation GuiObject

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Rece.documentation: Recenters the DataType.CFrame of the VR headset to the current orientation of the headset worn by the user

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.SetN: Whether the specified gamepad can move the GUI navigator

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.SetN.documentation: Sets whether or not the specified Enum.UserInputType can move the GuiObject navigator

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Devi.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user moves a device that has an accelerometer. Used to track real-world device movement within a Roblox game
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the force of gravity changes on a device that has an enabled accelerometer - such as a mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user rotates a device that has a gyroscope

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Game.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a gamepad is connected to the client. Passes the ''gamepadNum'' of the gamepad that was connected
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a gamepad is disconnected from the client. Passes the Enum.UserInputType of the gamepad that was disconnected

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Inpu.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device - such as a mouse or gamepad
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user changes how they're interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Jump.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires whenever the client makes a request for their character to jump

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Last.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Poin.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when the user performs a specific pointer action (wheel, pinch, pan).

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Text.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the client loses focus on a TextBox
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when the client focuses on a TextBox

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Touc.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user releases their finger from the screen on a TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of a mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of a mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user moves their finger on a TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of an Apple iPad or iPhone or a Google Android phone
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a UserInputService.TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of an mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a UserInputService.TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of a mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a user rotates two fingers on a UserInputService.TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of a mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user places their finger on a TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of an Apple iPad or iPhone or a Google Android phone
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a UserInputService.TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of a mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when a user taps their finger on a UserInputService.TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of a mobile device
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a user taps the game world on a UserInputService.TouchEnabled device - such as the screen of a mobile device

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.User.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when the DataType.CFrame of a specified Virtual Reality device changes

@roblox/globaltype/UserInputService.Wind.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when the window of the Roblox client loses focus on the user’s screen
Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when the window of the Roblox client gains focus on the user’s screen

@roblox/globaltype/UserService.documentation: A service that handles queries regarding users on the Roblox platform.

@roblox/globaltype/UserService.GetUserIn: An array of dictionary objects that contain the user's names

@roblox/globaltype/UserService.GetUserIn.documentation: Returns an array of user information including user name and display name.

@roblox/globaltype/UserSettings.documentation: A singleton object that houses basic user settings, which persist across all games on Roblox.

@roblox/globaltype/UserSettings.IsUserFe.documentation: Returns true if the specified user feature is enabled. This will throw an error if the user feature does not exist.

@roblox/globaltype/UserSettings.Reset.documentation: Erases the saved state of the UserSettings, and restores its default values.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Curve.documentation: Represents a 3D vector curve, it groups 3 FloatCurve, stored as 3 FloatCurve children instances.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Curve.GetValue.documentation: Samples the 3 FloatCurves (X, Y, Z) at the time passed as argument. Returns the 3 samples as a tuple of 3 numbers. If a channel curve is missing or no key is found in the curve the channel is evaluated as nil.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Curve.X.documentation: Returns the FloatCurve controlling the X channel. It is the first child instance of type FloatCurve named X. If none is found an empty FloatCurve is created.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Curve.Y.documentation: Returns the FloatCurve controlling the Y channel. It is the first child instance of type FloatCurve named Y. If none is found an empty FloatCurve is created.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Curve.Z.documentation: Returns the FloatCurve controlling the Z channel. It is the first child instance of type FloatCurve named Z. If none is found an empty FloatCurve is created.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Value.documentation: A container object for a single Vector3 value.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Value.Changed..documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/Vector3Value.changed..documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/VectorForce.documentation: A constraint used to apply a force to a part or assembly of parts

@roblox/globaltype/VectorForce.ApplyAtCe: Whether the force is applied at the center of mass of VectorForce/Attachment0|Attachment0’s parent Part
@roblox/globaltype/VectorForce.Force: The strength and direction of the force.
@roblox/globaltype/VectorForce.RelativeT: The DataType.CFrame in which the force is expressed
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.AreHinges: Displays how many hinges are detected by the VehicleSeat. Useful for debugging vehicle designs.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.Disabled: Toggles whether the VehicleSeat is active or not.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.HeadsUpDi: If true, a fancy speed bar will be displayed speed on screen that tells you what speed the Vehicle is moving at.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.MaxSpeed: The maximum speed that can be attained.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.Occupant: The humanoid that is sitting in the seat
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.Steer: The direction of movement, tied to the keys A and D. Must be one of 1 (right), 0 (straight), or -1 (left). Will refresh back to 0 unless constantly set.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.SteerFloa: Functions identically to VehicleSeat.Steer, but the value is not an integer.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.Throttle: The direction of movement, tied to the keys W and S. Must be an integer 1 (forward) 0 (null) or -1 (reverse). Will refresh back to 0 unless constantly set.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.ThrottleF: Functions identically to VehicleSeat.Throttle, but the value is not an integer.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.Torque: How fast the vehicles will be able to attain VehicleSeat.MaxSpeed. The greater the number, the faster it will reach the maximum speed.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.TurnSpeed: The speed at which the vehicle will turn. Higher numbers can cause problems and are not necessarily better.
@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.Sit/param: The humanoid being forced to sit in the VehicleSeat

@roblox/globaltype/VehicleSeat.Sit.documentation: Forces the character with the specified Humanoid to sit in the VehicleSeat.

@roblox/globaltype/VelocityMotor.Current: Displays the angle that the motor is at in radians.
@roblox/globaltype/VelocityMotor.Desired: The desired angle to be reached. The motor will attempt to reach this angle.
@roblox/globaltype/VelocityMotor.MaxVelo: The maximum amount of velocity able to be reached.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.documentation: A GUI object that renders a rectangle, like a Frame does, with a moving video image

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.IsLoaded: Indicates when the VideoFrame.Video has loaded from Roblox servers and is ready to play.
@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Looped: Sets whether or not the VideoFrame.Video repeats once it has finished when it is playing
@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Playing: Indicates whether the VideoFrame.Video is currently playing. It can be set to start or pause playback
@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Resolution: Gets the original source resolution of the VideoFrame.Video file
@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.TimeLength: Indicates the length of the VideoFrame.Video in seconds
@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.TimePositi: Indicates the progress in seconds of the VideoFrame.Video
@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Video: The content ID of the video file a VideoFrame object is associated with.
@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Volume: Indicates how loud the VideoFrame.Video is currently playing back

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Pause.documentation: Sets VideoFrame.Playing to false, pausing playback if the VideoFrame.Video is playing.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Play.documentation: Sets VideoFrame.Playing to true, playing the VideoFrame.Video from the current Video.TimePosition

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.DidLoop.Co.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.DidLoop.Wa.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Ended.Conn.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Ended.Wait.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Ended.documentation: Fires when the VideoFrame.Video has completed playback and stopped.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Loaded.Con.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Loaded.Wai.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Paused.Con.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Paused.Wai.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Paused.documentation: This event fires whenever the VideoFrame.Video is paused using VideoFrame:Pause or by setting VideoFrame.Playing to false

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Played.Con.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Played.Wai.documentation: Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/VideoFrame.Played.documentation: Fires whenever the VideoFrame.Video is played using the VideoFrame:Play function or by setting VideoFrame.Playing to true

@roblox/globaltype/ViewportFrame.Ambient: The lighting hue applied to the area within the ViewportFrame
@roblox/globaltype/ViewportFrame.Current: Camera that is used to render children objects
@roblox/globaltype/ViewportFrame.ImageCo: Determines how a rendered image will be colorized
@roblox/globaltype/ViewportFrame.ImageTr: Determines the transparency of the rendered image
@roblox/globaltype/ViewportFrame.LightDi: A DataType.Vector3 representing the direction of the light source from the position 0, 0, 0

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualInputManager.documentation: An internal service that offers no functionality to developers.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.documentation: VirtualUser is a service that allows you to record the inputs of a user, and then play it back to a limited extent.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.Button1Do.documentation: Simulates the user holding the left mouse button down.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.Button1Up.documentation: Simulates the user releasing the left mouse button.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.Button2Do.documentation: Simulates the user holding the right mouse button down.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.Button2Up.documentation: Simulates the user releasing the right mouse button.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.CaptureCo.documentation: Attempts to gain priority over the hardware controller's input, in favor of the VirtualUser's simulated input.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.ClickButt.documentation: Simulates the user clicking the left mouse button.
Simulates the user clicking the right mouse button.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.MoveMouse.documentation: Simulates the user moving the mouse cursor to a specific position.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.SetKeyDow.documentation: Simulates the user holding a key down.

@roblox/globaltype/VirtualUser.StopRecor.documentation: Stops recording the user's input. Returns a Lua script as a string, that allows you to playback the inputs that were recorded.

@roblox/globaltype/Visit.documentation: The Visit service is a backend service used by Roblox. Its functions are not accessible to developers in any form.

@roblox/globaltype/VoiceChatService.IsVo.documentation: Returns whether or not the given user has voice enabled.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.documentation: The VRService is a service that is responsible for handling interactions between Roblox and Virtual Reality.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.GuiInputUse: Describes what UserCFrame is responsible for input in VR.
@roblox/globaltype/VRService.VREnabled: Describes whether the user is using a virtual reality device

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.GetTouchpad.documentation: Returns the VRTouchpadMode indicating the mode of a specified VRTouchpad.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.GetUserCFra.documentation: Returns a CFrame describing the position & orientation of a specified virtual reality device.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.GetUserCFra: A boolean indicating whether the specified VR device is enabled (true) or disabled (false).

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.GetUserCFra.documentation: Returns true if the specified UserCFrame is available to be listened to.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.RecenterUse.documentation: Recenters the CFrame to the current location of the VR headset being worn by the user.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.RequestNavi: The VR device for which the navigation is requested.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.RequestNavi.documentation: Requests navigation to the specified DataType.CFrame, using the specified Enum.UserCFrame as the origin for the visualizer parabola.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.SetTouchpad: The specified VRTouchpad you want to set the mode of.
The mode you want to set the specified VRTouchpad to.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.SetTouchpad.documentation: Sets the mode of the specified VRTouchpad to the specified VRTouchpadMode.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.NavigationR.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fired when navigation is requested from the VRService.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.TouchpadMod.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires if the VRTouchpadMode of a VRTouchpad is changed.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.UserCFrameC.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.

@roblox/globaltype/VRService.UserCFrameE.documentation: Connects the given function to the event and returns an RBXScriptConnection that represents it.
Yields the current thread until the signal is fired and returns the parameters provided by the signal.
Fires when a UserCFrame gets enabled or disabled.

@roblox/globaltype/WeldConstraint.documentation: Joins two BasePart together such that their relative position and orientation remain the same.

@roblox/globaltype/WeldConstraint.Active: Indicates if the WeldConstraint is currently active in the world
@roblox/globaltype/WeldConstraint.Part0: The first part connected by the constraint.
@roblox/globaltype/WeldConstraint.Part1: The second part connected by the constraint.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.documentation: The Workspace is the service in which any objects that are to be rendered in the 3D world exist. Objects not descending from Workspace will not be rendered or physically interact with the world

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.AllowThirdP: Determines whether assets created by other uses can be sold in the game.
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.CurrentCame: The Camera object being used by the local player.
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.Distributed: The amount of time, in seconds, that the game has been running.
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.FallenParts: Determines the height at which falling BasePart (and their ancestor Model) are destroyed
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.Gravity: Determines the acceleration due to gravity applied to falling BaseParts.
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.PhysicsStep: Sets how the solver will advance the physics simulation forward in time.
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.StreamingEn: Whether content streaming is enabled for the place
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.StreamingMi: Minimum distance that content will be streamed to players with high priority
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.StreamingPa: Whether streaming physics pause mode is active
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.StreamingTa: Maximum distance that content will be streamed to players
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.Terrain: A reference to the Terrain object parented to the Workspace
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.TouchesUseC: Determines whether BasePart in different groups set to not collide will ignore collisions and touch events
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.FilteringEn: Determines whether changes made from the client will replicate to the server or not.
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.BreakJoints: An array of BaseParts for whom joints are to be broken.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.BreakJoints.documentation: Goes through all BaseParts given, breaking any joints connected to these parts.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.Experimenta: True if the experimental solver is to be enabled.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.Experimenta.documentation: Returns true if the game has the PGS Physics solver enabled.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.GetNumAwake.documentation: Returns the number of BaseParts that are deemed physically active, due to being recently under the influence of physics.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.GetPhysicsT: The percentage of real-time that physics simulation is currently being throttled to.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.GetPhysicsT.documentation: Returns an integer, between 0 and 100, representing the percentage of real-time that physics simulation is currently being throttled to.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.GetRealPhys: Returns the number of frames per second that physics is currently being simulated at.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.GetRealPhys.documentation: Returns the number of frames per second that physics is currently being simulated at.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.GetServerTi.documentation: Returns the server epoch time in seconds

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.JoinToOutsi: An array of BaseParts for whom joints are to be made.

The Enum.JointCreationMode to be used. Passing in enum/JointCreationMode|Enum.JointCreationMode.All or enum/JointCreationMode|Enum.JointCreationMode.Surface has the same behavior which equates to Join Always

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.JoinToOutsi.documentation: Creates joints between the specified BasePart and any touching parts depending on the parts' surfaces and the specified joint creation mode.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.MakeJoints/: An array of BasePart for whom joints are to be made

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.MakeJoints.documentation: Goes through all BaseParts given. If any part's side has a Enum.SurfaceType that can make a joint it will create a joint with any adjacent parts.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.PGSIsEnable: True if the PGS solver is enabled.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.PGSIsEnable.documentation: Returns true if the game has the PGS Physics solver enabled.

@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.SetPhysicsT: Whether or not physics throttling is enabled.
@roblox/globaltype/Workspace.UnjoinFromO: An array of BaseParts for whom joints are to be broken.
